&lt;p&gt;The correct option is&lt;strong&gt; The kid begged her mother not to leave her alone there.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;Direct speech, &lt;/strong&gt;and we have to convert it into&lt;strong&gt; Indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In indirect speech, the tense, pronouns, and time expressions are changed according to the rules of reported speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;First, we change the reporting verb &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;told&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; into the reporting verb &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;begged&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; to convey the sense of request in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then we change the pronoun &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;me&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; to &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;her&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; because we are reporting someone else&amp;#39;s words.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Next, we have to change the tense of the reported speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;don&amp;#39;t&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;not to&amp;#39;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is followed by V1 form of the verb&lt;strong&gt; i.e. leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally, we change &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;here&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;there&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;because we are reporting what someone said in a different location.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Therefore, the correct conversion is:&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The kid begged her mother not to leave her alone there.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The original direct speech is in present tense and indicates a kid requesting her mother not to leave her alone.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is not suitable because it keeps the tense of the statement the same without changing it to past tense and so is incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3 &lt;/strong&gt;is not suitable because it keeps the location &amp;lsquo;here&amp;rsquo; as it is but in indirect tense it should change to &amp;lsquo;there&amp;rsquo; thus making it incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4 &lt;/strong&gt;is not suitable because it changes the tense to present tense but in indirect speech it should be past tense, making it the incorrect option.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;Option (1)&lt;/strong&gt; is the suitable option.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &lt;u&gt;option 2)&lt;/u&gt; i.e. &lt;u&gt;The landlady told the tenant that every room was fitted with an electric fan.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is an &lt;strong&gt;assertive&lt;/strong&gt; sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;We change an assertive sentence in direct into indirect by making the following changes:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The reporting verb &amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; becomes&lt;strong&gt; told.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Comma and inverted commas are removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used after the object(tenant) of the reporting verb.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;becomes&lt;strong&gt; was.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Present changes into the Past.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Past Tense of &amp;#39;is&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Eventually, we will get the final sentence- &amp;quot;The landlady told the tenant that every room was fitted with an electric fan.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is&lt;u&gt; option 1)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;i.e.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt; Raja told&amp;nbsp;Suraj that he was waiting for him.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is an&lt;strong&gt; assertive&lt;/strong&gt; sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It will be changed into Indirect speech &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;by making the following changes:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Comma and inverted commas are removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &lt;strong&gt;that &lt;/strong&gt;is used.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;First person pronouns in the direct speech change according to the subject(Raja) of the reporting verb(said&amp;#39;. Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;he&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Present tense is changed to&lt;b&gt; past. Hence, &amp;#39;am waiting&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;was waiting&amp;#39;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sometimes&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong&gt;object of reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; is not mentioned&amp;nbsp;but it can be guessed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, we know that the object of the reporting verb is Suraj.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eventually, we get the final sentence-&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;   background-&quot;&gt;Raja told Suraj that he was waiting for him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;how&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The&lt;strong&gt; sentence ends&lt;/strong&gt; with a &lt;strong&gt;sign of interrogation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; blank is to be filled &lt;/strong&gt;in&lt;strong&gt; with&lt;/strong&gt; an&lt;strong&gt; interrogative adverb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&amp;#39;s consider the usage of the words given &lt;/strong&gt;in the options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How:&lt;/strong&gt; It is used to ask about&amp;nbsp;the process of some action.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why:&lt;/strong&gt; This word asks the reason of some action.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where:&lt;/strong&gt; this word asks the place of some action.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What:&lt;/strong&gt; This word asks about the things or actions, what were they&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dare&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;means&lt;/strong&gt; to&lt;strong&gt; show courage.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This courage maybe for a good or bad deed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thus the correct word is&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;how&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An interrogative adverb is always put at the beginning of the sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The completed sentence is:&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;How &lt;/u&gt;dare you say so?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;about whom&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; blank is to be filled in&lt;/strong&gt; with a&lt;strong&gt; relative pronoun.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relative Pronoun: &lt;/strong&gt;A pronoun which relates the noun&amp;nbsp;to the other part of the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;whom&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is the pronoun here.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;about&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is the preposition.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rule:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When the relative pronoun is used in the objective case and a preposition is used before the pronoun, the use of the relative pronoun makes the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct answer here is&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;about whom&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The complete sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt; He is the publisher&lt;u&gt; about whom &lt;/u&gt;I was talking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;He asked me whether I knew Melanie&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is a type of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yes/no&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;question.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Yes/no&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;question expect yes or no as the answer&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While converting such sentences to indirect speech,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;if&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;whether&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The third form of the verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used in indirect speech&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;knew&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(in indirect speech) is used in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;know&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(in direct speech)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yes/no&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;question is different from a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Wh- question.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(22, 22, 22);&quot;&gt;In a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yes-no question&lt;/span&gt;, the quoted question begins with an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;auxiliary verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;form such as&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ital&quot; style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;is, are, am, do, does, has, have, can, will.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And the expected answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yes or no.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Wh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;questions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;questions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;that begin with&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;wh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;rdquo; words:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;who, whose, what, when, which, why, where, and how.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;​The correct sentence is,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;He asked me whether I knew Melanie.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I remember my mother taking me to the zoo.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​​The process&amp;nbsp;of transformation of these kinds of sentences as follows:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of &lt;strong&gt;Gerund&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infinitives, gerunds, and participles&lt;/strong&gt; can also have &lt;strong&gt;passive&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;forms&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;I hate people lying to me.&amp;nbsp;(Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;I hate being lied to.&amp;nbsp;(Passive Voice)&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, in the given question &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;being taken&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;taking&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;progressive&lt;/strong&gt; form of the &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; is changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;being + V3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;active to passive&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; transformation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The object&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;My mother&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used as a &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The preposition &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I remember my mother taking me to the zoo.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Transformation of Infinitives:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject+is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had+to+V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;+Object.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject(Objective case)+is/am/are/was/were/has/have/had+to+be+V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;+by+object(subjective case).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your child is to learn chess. (Active Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Chess is to be learned by your child. (Passive Voice)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/01/hin1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 200px; height: 92px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Passive voice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है।&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;सवाल के अनुसार हमें इसे&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Active voice&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदलना होगा&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों के परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया निम्नानुसार है:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Gerund&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का एक उदाहरण है।&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Infinatics, gerunds, और participles के&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Passive form&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;भी हो सकते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां दिए गए प्रश्न में&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;being taken&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;को&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;taking&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में बदल दिया जाएगा&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;के&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;रूप में&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;My mother&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उपयोग किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;By&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;preposition हटा दिया जाएगा&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ram told Gopal that he had visited that place three months before.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence is in the &lt;strong&gt;past tense&lt;/strong&gt; and thus while &lt;strong&gt;changing&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong&gt;reported speech&lt;/strong&gt; the tense becomes &lt;strong&gt;past perfect&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;past perfect&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;refers to a time earlier than before now. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;It is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;used&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to make it clear that&lt;strong&gt; one event happened before&lt;/strong&gt; another in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;past&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);  &quot;&gt;In this sentence, it refers to&lt;strong&gt; incidents&lt;/strong&gt; that took place &lt;strong&gt;three months&lt;/strong&gt; before.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Ago&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;before&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; while converting to &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; first person pronoun &amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;he&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; while &lt;strong&gt;reporting&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ram told Gopal that he had visited that place three months before.&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Some rules of changing &lt;strong&gt;reported speech&lt;/strong&gt; from&lt;strong&gt; direct&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech &lt;/strong&gt;are as follows:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simple present&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;simple past&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Direct:&amp;nbsp;The teacher said, &amp;ldquo;Keep quiet&amp;nbsp;.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Indirect:&amp;nbsp;The teacher asked us to keep quiet&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;When &lt;strong&gt;reporting verb&lt;/strong&gt; is in&lt;strong&gt; Future&amp;nbsp;tense&lt;/strong&gt; then there will be&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;no change&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; or&lt;strong&gt; tense&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;strong&gt;Reported speech&lt;/strong&gt; in the sentence.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Direct:&amp;nbsp;The teacher says, &amp;ldquo;Tom will&amp;nbsp;perform&amp;nbsp;on the stage&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
		Indirect:&amp;nbsp;The teacher says that Tom will&amp;nbsp;perform&amp;nbsp;on the stage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;When the &lt;strong&gt;Reporting speech &lt;/strong&gt;has&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Universal Truth&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Habitual fact&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;then there is &lt;strong&gt;no change&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;Tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Direct: My teacher, &amp;ldquo;The earth&amp;nbsp;is round&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
		Indirect: My&amp;nbsp;teacher said that the earth&amp;nbsp;is round.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;When &lt;strong&gt;Reporting speech&lt;/strong&gt; has&amp;nbsp;some&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Imagined Condition&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;then there is &lt;strong&gt;no change&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;Tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Direct:&amp;nbsp;He said, &amp;ldquo;If I were rich, I would help him.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
		Indirect: He said that if he were rich he would help him.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;record their experiences​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​​.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In a sentence, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is used according to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;person and number.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;always&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conforms to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;main subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;plural&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;noun &amp;#39;writers&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;suggests that the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;verb &lt;/span&gt;and the &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronoun&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;must also be&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;plural.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;verb &amp;#39;record&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and the &lt;strong&gt;pronoun &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;their&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;will be the correct choice&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;underlined&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given question.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus the&lt;strong&gt; 4th option&lt;/strong&gt; will be the correct choice.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;In journals, writers &lt;strong&gt;record their experiences&lt;/strong&gt; and reflect on their value or importance.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;QRSP&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;Q &lt;/strong&gt;will &lt;strong&gt;follow &lt;/strong&gt;sentence &lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt;, as it starts with a&amp;nbsp;relative pronoun &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;who&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;which refers to the &lt;strong&gt;noun mentioned&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;earlier.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here you can note that sentences &lt;strong&gt;S and P &lt;/strong&gt;form &lt;strong&gt;a pair &lt;/strong&gt;talking about &lt;strong&gt;safety standards.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;S6 &lt;/strong&gt;will &lt;strong&gt;follow &lt;/strong&gt;sentence &lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;, as the pronoun &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;refers to the &lt;strong&gt;safety standards &lt;/strong&gt;discussed in sentence &lt;strong&gt;P.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this way, sentence &lt;strong&gt;R &lt;/strong&gt;will be used in &lt;strong&gt;between &lt;/strong&gt;sentence &lt;strong&gt;Q and S&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct answer is: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;i&gt;QRSP&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Here the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;massacre &lt;/strong&gt;is used as a &lt;strong&gt;noun &lt;/strong&gt;and its meaning is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;act&quot;&gt;act&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;killing&quot;&gt;killing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a lot of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;people&quot;&gt;people.&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-weight: 700;&quot; title=&quot;people&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;He&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-style: italic;&quot; title=&quot;ordered&quot;&gt;ordered&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the massacre of 2,000 women and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;query&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;    font-style: italic;&quot; title=&quot;children&quot;&gt;children&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(29, 42, 87);   font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ram tells me that I am dull​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;basic rules&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for changing or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;converting direct speech into indirect speech:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;commas, inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;removed,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;added&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;says to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; becomes &amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tells&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;second-person pronoun&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; becomes the &lt;strong&gt;first-person pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;I&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39; and the &lt;strong&gt;second-person singular present verb &amp;#39;are&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be &lt;strong&gt;replaced by&lt;/strong&gt; the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;first-person singular present &amp;#39;am&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;CBAD&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; comes first as it introduces that the&lt;strong&gt; recipe of a dish&lt;/strong&gt; is described in the paragraph.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B &lt;/strong&gt;follows C as it tells that &lt;strong&gt;the vegetable bits were cut into long strips after being washed&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A &lt;/strong&gt;follows B as it states that after cutting, &lt;strong&gt;the bits were put in a huge pot&lt;/strong&gt; and were placed to cook on the fire.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; follows A as it describes that after all this,&lt;strong&gt; the cook ground some fresh coconut, green chillies and garlic together&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;C:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;He took all the&amp;nbsp;vegetable bits, washed&amp;nbsp;them and cleaned them&amp;nbsp;well.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Then he cut them into&amp;nbsp;long strips.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;He put them&amp;nbsp;in a huge pot and placed&amp;nbsp;it on the fire to cook.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Next, he ground some&amp;nbsp;fresh coconut, green&amp;nbsp;chillies and garlic&amp;nbsp;together.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Important Rules to Solve the Para Jumbles:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Read the sentences attentively and try&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to comprehend the idea or theme&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the paragraph and eliminate the irrelevant options.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Try to identify the opening&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(independent sentence)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and closing sentences of the paragraph&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(concluding sentence)&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Try to identify&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the mandatory pairs&lt;/span&gt;. Two sentences can be connected through various&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;connectors&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and other&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;determinants&lt;/span&gt;. Identify the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;connecting the sentences with one&amp;nbsp;other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;CDAB&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; comes first as it is independent of any other sentence and introduces the matter of concern, i.e., &lt;strong&gt;bones&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; follows&lt;strong&gt; C&lt;/strong&gt; as it asks &lt;strong&gt;a question that opposes the idea given in C&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt; as it states that the elbow can be bent because&lt;strong&gt; it is not one single bone&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B &lt;/strong&gt;follows &lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt; as it further describes that &lt;strong&gt;the elbow is different bones&amp;nbsp;joined together at the elbow&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​C:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Bones cannot be bent.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;how do we bend our elbow?&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It is not one long bone from the upper arm to our wrist.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;It is different bones joined together at the elbow.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Important Rules to Solve the Para Jumbles:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Read the sentences attentively and try&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to comprehend the idea or theme&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the paragraph and eliminate the irrelevant options.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Try to identify the opening&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(independent sentence)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and closing sentences of the paragraph&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(concluding sentence)&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Try to identify&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the mandatory pairs&lt;/span&gt;. Two sentences can be connected through various&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;connectors&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and other&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;determinants&lt;/span&gt;. Identify the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;connecting the sentences with one&amp;nbsp;other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;S, P, R, Q​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage56.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 150px; height: 40px;&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;introductory clause&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is already given in the question that mentions&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the topic &amp;#39;Things being different from the common perception&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence S tells us the perception of us being at rest.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It&amp;nbsp;will be put in the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;first place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence P&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;addresses&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the actual scenario where we are moving at around 2.1 kilometres per hour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;It will be put in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;second place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence R&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;takes the story forward&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;by mentioning the factors which aren&amp;#39;t included in calculating the above-mentioned speed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It will be put in&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;third place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The last sentence is Q&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as it mentions&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the distance that we might have traveled while reading the current paragraph.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thus, the&amp;nbsp;correct order is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Things are often not what they seem.&amp;nbsp;As you read this sentence, perhaps sitting in a comfortable chair in your study, you would probably consider yourself at rest.&amp;nbsp;But you are really not, because the Milky Way galaxy, of which you are a part, is moving through space at 2.1 million kilometres an hour.&amp;nbsp;And that is without taking into account the effects of earth&amp;#39;s rotation on its own axis, its orbiting around the sun and the sun&amp;#39;s journey around the Milky Way.&amp;nbsp;So in roughly twenty&amp;nbsp;seconds that it would have taken you to read this paragraph, you have already moved thousands of kilometre.&amp;nbsp;This happened without you even knowing it. So imagine the changes that occur to this earth and humanity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;DBCA&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While arranging the parts of the passage, &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;we should find some grammatical or contextual connections between them&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;-

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D follows sentence 1&lt;/strong&gt; as sentence 1 introduces the religion&amp;nbsp;Buddhism and its founder and sentence D further gives the description about&amp;nbsp;Siddharth Gautam.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentences B and C&lt;/strong&gt; form a mandatory pair as they mean that although&amp;nbsp;Buddhism had no God in the beginning, later on, the followers of this religion developed&amp;nbsp;Buddha, Bodhisattvas, Arhats and Deities as their God.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A is the last sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it forms a mandatory pair with &lt;strong&gt;sentence 6.&lt;/strong&gt; In sentence 6, the pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;this&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is referred to &amp;#39;Nirvana&amp;#39;. It means that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Nirvana&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is to&amp;nbsp;free oneself from the cycle of birth, death and rebirth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Thus, the correct order is DBCA:&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_640E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_632E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Buddhism as a religion developed from the teachings of Siddharth Gautam.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Gautam Buddha or Buddha as commonly known was born in 520 BCE in North East India.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Initially the religion had no God as in other religions of that time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C: &lt;/strong&gt;But later on the followers developed Buddha, Bodhisattvas, Arhats and Deities as God.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The real goal of Buddhism is to attain Nirvana.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;This is to free oneself from the cycle of birth, death and rebirth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct sequence for the given sentences is &lt;b&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DBAC&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D&lt;/strong&gt; comes first as it is independent of any other statement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B&lt;/strong&gt; follows&lt;strong&gt; D&lt;/strong&gt; as it states that of all the persons we like, there is someone whom we like the most.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt; as it tells that the speaker dislikes his neighbour the most.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt; as it states the name of the speaker&amp;#39;s neighbour.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Thus, the sequence becomes:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;D:&lt;/strong&gt; We like some persons.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B:&lt;/strong&gt; We like someone the most.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A:&lt;/strong&gt; Similarly, the person I dislike the most is my neighbour.&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C:&lt;/strong&gt; He is Mr. Kant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;DBAC&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;(A) is unambiguous and (B) is grammatically correct&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;A &lt;/strong&gt;says:&lt;strong&gt; I love Ethan Hunt &amp;gt; I love you&lt;/strong&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Thus, there is no other way in which it can be interpreted. So, it is &lt;strong&gt;unambiguous&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;B &lt;/strong&gt;says: &lt;strong&gt;I was scared because of being followed by a stranger&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There is no grammatical mistake or any ambiguity in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Thus, the &lt;strong&gt;correct&lt;/strong&gt; answer is option &lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;39px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImage6.png&quot; width=&quot;210px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One might think that Sentence &lt;strong&gt;A &lt;/strong&gt;should be interpreted as following:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I love Ethan Hunt &amp;gt; You love Ethan Hunt.&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;But the above meaning&amp;nbsp;would be possible if Sentence A were:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51);   background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;I love Ethan Hunt more than you &lt;strong&gt;do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;He requested her to accomplish the task&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;basic rules&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for changing or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;converting direct speech into indirect speech:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;commas, inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;removed&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verbs such as &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; etc. change to &amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;requested, ordered, suggested &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;advised&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Please&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; indicates a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;request&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and therefore, &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;requested&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;should be used here.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;imperative mood in the direct speech changes into the infinitive in the indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/confusion-points-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Confusion Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You may think the past tense form of the verb&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;accomplished&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;should be used.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;wrong&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because the past form of the verb&amp;nbsp;cannot be used as the infinitive should be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The indirect speech of the given sentence is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Deepak told me that he would come to the office the next day.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When the reporting speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;Simple&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;Future&amp;nbsp;Tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;then all the speech&amp;nbsp;Changes to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;Present Conditional tense&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Said to&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;the reporting verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;changes&amp;nbsp;into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;told&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;Replace&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;comma (,) and inverted commas (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with the conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;The first person (I)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in reported speech changes according to the subject of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;reporting clause(Deepak).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;color: inherit !important; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;The adverb of time(Tomorrow)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the reporting speech changes&amp;nbsp;into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; background-color: inherit !important;&quot;&gt;the next day.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Deepak told me that he would come to the office the next day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Will&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;shall&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; both change into&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;would&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; unless the sentence shows the sense of &lt;strong&gt;suggestion/duty.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;I said to Hansa, &amp;quot;I shall go to Mumbai&amp;quot;. (Direct Speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;I told Hansa that I would go to Mumbai. (Indirect speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Change in adverbs&amp;nbsp;and determines in Direct To Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Adverbs in &amp;#39;direct speech&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Adverbs in &amp;#39;indirect speech&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Now&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Then&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Today&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Here&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;There&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;This&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;These&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Those&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Ago&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Before&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Today&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;That day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Tomorrow&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;The next day&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Why didn&amp;#39;t you tell me that?&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Wh questions&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;are questions starting with &lt;strong&gt;WH words.&lt;/strong&gt; They include:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What, when, where, who, whom, which, why, how.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Questions words are used to ask about specific qualities, times, places, people.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Structure of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;WH questions with an auxiliary verbs: Wh word +auxiliary&amp;nbsp; verb+ subject + main verb + ?.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Who is he?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The formation of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;WH questions&amp;#39; without any auxiliary verbs: Wh word + main verb + ?&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;What hit the dog?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the above explanation&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Why didn&amp;#39;t you tell me that?&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is grammatically correct. Here a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;auxiliary&lt;/strong&gt; verb&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;didn&amp;#39;t&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is used after the &amp;#39;Wh word&amp;#39; which is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verb that follows &amp;#39;did&amp;#39; should be used in its base form, thus, &amp;#39;tell&amp;#39; will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt; will be the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;interrogative sentence&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is used to form &lt;strong&gt;yes/no questions.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The construction of an interrogative sentence is: &lt;strong&gt;modal/auxiliary verb + subject + main verb...?.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;An interrogative sentence&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;always begins with an &lt;strong&gt;auxiliary verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Were the dogs barking?&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Do you go to school?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Auxiliary verbs are helping verbs ( not main verbs).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Common auxiliary verbs include&lt;strong&gt; be, do, have.&lt;/strong&gt; Others are&lt;strong&gt; will, must, shall, would, may, might, could&lt;/strong&gt;, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Ram is a good man.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s explore options:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The statement in &lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt; is an example of interrogative sentence.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The structure for it is: &lt;strong&gt;wh- word+ subject+ auxiliary verb+ other info.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In the given statement the &lt;strong&gt;error lies in the usage of auxiliary verb &amp;#39;is&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The auxiliary verb isn&amp;#39;t following&amp;nbsp;subject, here in the sentence the subject is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;time&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;which makes this statement incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The statement in &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is an example of apostrophe usage.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The meaning of apostrophe is a mark &amp;#39; used to indicate the omission of letters or figures, the possessive case (as in &amp;#39;John&amp;#39;s book&amp;#39;), or the plural of letters or figures (as in &amp;#39;the 1960&amp;#39;s&amp;#39;).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here, in the sentence the apostrophe mark is &lt;strong&gt;not used to show the possession which makes the statement incorrect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The statement in &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt; is an example of simple present tense.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The structure for it:&lt;strong&gt; Subject+ do/does+ not+ the first form of verb+ object.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;From the structure, we can say that the &lt;strong&gt;usage of &amp;#39;needs&amp;#39; is incorrect &lt;/strong&gt;in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The statement in &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt; is grammatically and contextually correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject of the sentence, i.e. &amp;#39;Ram&amp;#39; is singular and is succeeded by singular verb.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;QSRP&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given question is an example of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Para Jumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that the first statement of a para jumbled question is usually&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an independent general statement, a noun, a universal fact, starting of an incident, or it starts with &amp;#39;most&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;once&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence Q&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be the first sentence because it is an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;introductory&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence S&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the next sentence because it tells us what the authorities did afterwards&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence R&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be the next sentence because it tells us what happened in between. What the air quality resulted.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Sentence P&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct sequence is:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;The air quality in Melbourne deteriorated to the worst in the world as smoke from massive bushfires engulfed Australia&amp;#39;s second biggest city.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;As a result, the Australian health authorities have issued warnings, advising people to stay indoors and take precautionary measures.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;R&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Meanwhile, the raging bushfires, one of the worst in its history, has killed at least 26 people, burned over 10 million hectares of land, destroyed over 2000 homes and pushed many species towards extinction.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;P&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;However, some relief is expected as the Australian Broadcasting Corporation has predicted widespread rainfall for the east coast of the country starting 14 January 2020.&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sequence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The air quality in Melbourne deteriorated to the worst in the world as smoke from massive bushfires engulfed Australia&amp;#39;s second biggest city.&amp;nbsp;As a result, the Australian health authorities have issued warnings, advising people to stay indoors and take precautionary measures.&amp;nbsp;Meanwhile, the raging bushfires, one of the worst in its history, has killed at least 26 people, burned over 10 million hectares of land, destroyed over 2000 homes and pushed many species towards extinction.&amp;nbsp;However, some relief is expected as the Australian Broadcasting Corporation has predicted widespread rainfall for the east coast of the country starting 14 January 2020.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;certainly going&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to grammar, we need to use an adverb in between the auxiliary verb and the main verb.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence we need to use an adverb because &amp;#39;certain&amp;#39; is an adjective that is incorrect so we need to use &amp;#39;certainly&amp;#39; also, &amp;#39;go&amp;#39; is a base form that is incorrect we need to use present continuous tense as &amp;#39;am&amp;#39; is an auxiliary verb hence, &amp;#39;going&amp;#39; is the correct verb.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct sentence is-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I&amp;#39;m certainly going to start studying from today.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;व्याकरण (Grammar) के अनुसार, हमें सहायक क्रिया और मुख्य क्रिया के बीच में क्रिया विशेषण (Adjective) का उपयोग करने की आवश्यकता होती है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिए गए वाक्य (Sentence)&amp;nbsp;में हमें एक क्रिया विशेषण का उपयोग करने की आवश्यकता है क्योंकि &amp;#39;निश्चित&amp;#39; (Certain) एक विशेषण है जो गलत है इसलिए हमें &amp;#39;निश्चित रूप से&amp;#39; (Certainly) भी उपयोग करने की आवश्यकता है, &amp;#39;गो&amp;#39; (go)&amp;nbsp; एक आधार रूप है जो गलत है हमें वर्तमान निरंतर काल का उपयोग करने की आवश्यकता है जैसे &amp;#39;am &amp;#39; एक सहायक क्रिया है इसलिए &amp;#39;जाना&amp;#39; (going) सही क्रिया है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;तो सही वाक्य है&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I&amp;#39;m certainly going to start studying from today.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My Father gave me a piece of advices&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;noun&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is a word that names something, such as a person, place, thing, or idea.&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;For eg.-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Vedika, Iron, Honesty, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Advice&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is a noun meaning &amp;quot;an opinion or suggestion about what someone should do.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Advice is an uncountable&amp;nbsp;noun and thus it&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;does not&lt;/strong&gt; have a plural form.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The noun &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;advices&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is being used in a plural form which is incorrect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;advice &lt;/strong&gt;is a &lt;strong&gt;noun &lt;/strong&gt;whereas the word &lt;strong&gt;advise &lt;/strong&gt;is a &lt;strong&gt;verb &lt;/strong&gt;meaning to&amp;nbsp;offer suggestions about the best course of action to someone.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For eg.-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;I &lt;strong&gt;advised &lt;/strong&gt;him to go home.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Whom did you see?&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Whom&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;as the objective pronoun, receives the action. Here it is the object of &amp;#39;see&amp;#39;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex&lt;/span&gt;: Whom did you like.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is option&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;has a tense related mistake.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;saw &lt;/strong&gt;will be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;have seen&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Last night&lt;/strong&gt; is the adverb of past indefinite tense.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;the sentence is past indefinite tense, so we will use the second form of verb.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;we use &lt;strong&gt;for &lt;/strong&gt;instead of &lt;strong&gt;since&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For&lt;/strong&gt;: use for Period of time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Since&lt;/strong&gt;: used for Point of time&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;has an article related mistake.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;we use an article in this sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(68, 68, 68);   &quot;&gt;before a singular noun beginning with a vowel sound&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Appoint Arpit the monitor this time.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;The given sentence is &lt;strong&gt;an imperative sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;convert from the passive to the active form&lt;/strong&gt;, we need to &lt;strong&gt;follow some basic rules.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;First, we need to remove&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;let.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Second, use only &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;verb 1st form&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;be + verb 3rd form&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Now following the above-mentioned rules, the sentence would be -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Appoint Arpit the monitor this time.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Let&amp;#39;s understand the &lt;strong&gt;concept with some more examples.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let it be carried home.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Carry it home.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let the door be opened.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Open the door.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;BADC&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;independent&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of any other sentence as it is introducing or giving general information about&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an accounts officer&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;. Hence, &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first part&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will come after&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;it is giving information about the early stage career of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;the accounts officer who began his career as a peon&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;D&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will come after&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;it is giving information about how the man became an accounts officer from a peon i.e. by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gradually improving his qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;concludes&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;by saying that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the man learnt typing, accounting, and even done graduation to become an accounts officer&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Paragraph after rearranging the sentences&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Before he joined us as the accounts officer, he was a junior clerk.&amp;nbsp;In fact, he began his career as a peon in a small firm.&amp;nbsp;But he gradually improved his qualifications. He learnt typing, accounting and even graduated.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hint-text-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hint&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Rules to Solve the Para Jumbles&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Read the sentences&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;attentively and try to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comprehend the idea or theme of the sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;eliminate the irrelevant&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;options.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Try to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;identify the opening&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(independent sentence)&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;and closing sentences&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;(concluding sentence)&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Try to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;identify the mandatory pairs&lt;/span&gt;. Two sentences can be connected through various connectors and other determinants.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Did the court send you summons?&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the Passive Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;As per the given question we have to change the sentence into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process&amp;nbsp;of transformation of these kinds of sentences is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;you&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;becomes the &lt;strong&gt;object&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;active voice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The object&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;the court&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;becomes the &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;active voice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple past tense&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;changes in the following manner:-
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;was/were + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Active Voice -&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;(did&amp;nbsp;+ V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Here,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;were sent&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;did send&amp;#39;. (Passive to Active)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The preposition&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;You&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; will remain unchanged because &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is not changed when converting &lt;strong&gt;active to passive&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;passive to active.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​​&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Did the court send you summons?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य Passive Voice में है। दिए गए प्रश्न के अनुसार हमें वाक्य को Active Voice में बदलना है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इस प्रकार के वाक्यों के परिवर्तन की प्रक्रिया इस प्रकार है:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;active&amp;nbsp;voice&lt;/strong&gt; की वस्तु बन जाते हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;the court&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; &lt;strong&gt;active voice&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; बन जाती है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simple past tense &lt;/strong&gt;निम्नलिखित तरीके से बदलता है: -
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;was/were + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Active Voice -&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;(did&amp;nbsp;+ V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यहां, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;were sent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; को &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;did send&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; में बदल दिया जाएगा। (&lt;strong&gt;Passive to Active&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;by&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; हटा दिया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;You&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; अपरिवर्तित रहेगा क्योंकि &lt;strong&gt;active to passive&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;या &lt;strong&gt;passive to active&lt;/strong&gt; में परिवर्तित करने पर &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; नहीं बदला जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;but also by the men it honors, the men it remembers&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Not only &amp;hellip; but also&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used to connect and emphasize two phrases or two words at the same position.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Different Structures:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Adjective + but also + Adjective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Adverb + but also + Adverb&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Noun + but also + Noun&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + not only + Verb + but also + Verb&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I like&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;not only&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cheesecake&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but also&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cake.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but also by the men it honors, the men it remembers&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;should be used&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;u&gt;The Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;A nation reveals itself not only by the men it produces &lt;strong&gt;but also by the men it honors, the men it remembers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conjunction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a joiner, a word that connects (conjoins) parts of a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Coordinating conjunctions&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;join equals to one another.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Most children like sweets&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cookies.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Coordinating conjunctions go in between items joined, not at the beginning or end.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I like coffee,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;I don&amp;#39;t like tea.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Not only &amp;hellip; but also&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;एक ही स्थिति में दो वाक्यांशों या दो शब्दों को जोड़ने और उन पर जोर देने के लिए भी उपयोग किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;विभिन्न संरचनाएं:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Adjective + but also + Adjective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Adverb + but also + Adverb&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + Verb + not only + Noun + but also + Noun&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + not only + Verb + but also + Verb&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I like&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;not only&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cheesecake&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but also&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cake.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;अत: वाक्य को व्याकरणिक रूप से शुद्ध करने के लिए&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but also by the men it honors, the men it remembers&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;का प्रयोग करना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;Two of my sisters-in-law are staying with me&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;sister-in-law&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; is an example of a&lt;strong&gt; compound noun&lt;/strong&gt; which refers to&amp;nbsp;a noun made of two or more words.&amp;nbsp;Each word makes up part of the meaning of the noun.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&lt;strong&gt; compound nouns&lt;/strong&gt;, when &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is added to the main word,&lt;strong&gt; it becomes plural&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ex&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot; width: 300px;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;tbody&gt;
				&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Singular&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Plural&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;brother-in-law&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;brothers-in-law&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;mother-in-law&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;mothers-in-law&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;Member of Parliament&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;Members of Parliament&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Correct sentence is:&lt;strong&gt; Two of my sisters-in-law are staying with me.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&lt;strong&gt; option&amp;nbsp;1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He said that burglars had broken into his house the previous night&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is an example of an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentence&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in the form of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech&lt;/span&gt;. As per the question&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;we have to change it into indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Basic rules for changing or converting&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech into indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;:​
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Comma&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo; and &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted comma&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; are omitted in indirect speech and are often replaced by &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;that&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; clauses to form &amp;#39;that clauses&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;According to the reporting verb, changes are made in the direct sentence or the sentence in inverted commas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Said&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; will be no change&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;That&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; conjunction will be added to account for the comma and double-inverted commas (&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;starting a direct speech&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;burglars&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; will be no change&amp;nbsp;in the indirect speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Third-person (he/she/it/they)&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;any person&amp;#39;s name&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;no change&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;broke&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;had broken&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;in the indirect speech.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;past&amp;nbsp;simple to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;past perfect&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;my&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;his&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;in the indirect speech.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first-person &amp;gt; third-person&lt;/span&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;according to the subject of the reporting verb.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;The last night&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; will be changed into &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the previous night&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; in indirect speech. &lt;strong&gt;(change of time/adverbs direct form to indirect form)​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is the direct and indirect speech rule for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;assertive sentence&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;He said, &amp;quot;His girlfriend came yesterday.&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;(direct speech)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He said that his girlfriend had come the day before.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;(indirect speech)​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;He said that burglars had broken into his house the previous night&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct indirect form of the given sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;people used to think&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, the usage of &amp;quot;use to&amp;quot; is incorrect instead of this we need to use &amp;quot;used to&amp;quot; hence, the correct phrase is &amp;quot;people used to think.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;used to&amp;quot; is a modal verb that shows past habits. (done or experienced in the past, but no longer done or experienced)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see an example-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I used to eat meat, but now I&amp;rsquo;m a vegetarian.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct sentence is-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;In the olden days, many&lt;strong&gt; people used to think&lt;/strong&gt; that the earth was flat.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;She is reading the&amp;nbsp;novel titled White Tiger.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of a sentence in active voice is : &lt;strong&gt;subject + verb + object&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The active voice highlights the subject and the action performed by the verb.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The passive voice highlights the action performed by the verb which is received by the subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentences in active voice usually begin with the pronoun: &lt;strong&gt;He, She, They, We, i , It&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the correct answer, &lt;strong&gt;She&lt;/strong&gt;(subject) is &lt;strong&gt;reading&lt;/strong&gt;(verb) a &lt;strong&gt;novel&lt;/strong&gt;(object)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;CBDA&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In comparing all the statements after the rearrangement and establishing the logical flaw of the passage. The correct sequence is:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement C &lt;/strong&gt;is the opening line of the passage as it defines &lt;strong&gt;the field of criminology&lt;/strong&gt; and the theme of the passage which is &lt;strong&gt;crime and criminals&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement B&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; is the second line of the passage as it elaborates on the &lt;strong&gt;causes, correction, and prevention&lt;/strong&gt; of crime. This statement is incomplete by itself unless we link it with the first line of the passage.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement D &lt;/strong&gt;is the third line in the passage as it defines crime from a &lt;strong&gt;legal perspective&lt;/strong&gt;. This is also a &lt;strong&gt;specific &lt;/strong&gt;definition of crime from the&lt;strong&gt; legal point &lt;/strong&gt;of view and in contrast to the &lt;strong&gt;nonlegal &lt;/strong&gt;definition of criminology in the first line.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement A &lt;/strong&gt;is the final line of the passage as it starts with the phrase &amp;#39;by comparison&amp;#39; which establishes the link with the previous statement. The comparison is in terms of differences in viewpoints about crime between &lt;strong&gt;criminology and legal perspective&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; CBDA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct passage is:&lt;em&gt; C)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Criminology, scientific study of the nonlegal aspects of &lt;span&gt;crime&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span&gt;delinquency&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;strong&gt;B)&lt;/strong&gt; Including its causes, correction, and prevention, from the viewpoints of such &lt;span data-term=&quot;diverse&quot; data-type=&quot;MW&quot;&gt;diverse&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span data-term=&quot;disciplines&quot; data-type=&quot;MW&quot;&gt;disciplines&lt;/span&gt; as &lt;span&gt;anthropology&lt;/span&gt;, biology, &lt;span&gt;psychology, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D)&lt;/strong&gt; Viewed from a legal perspective, the term crime refers to individual criminal actions and the societal response to those actions. &lt;strong&gt;A)&lt;/strong&gt; By comparison, the field of criminology incorporates and examines broader knowledge about crime and criminals.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;​&lt;/span&gt;Bigot&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meanings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given options:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bigot:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person who has strong, unreasonable ideas, esp. about race or religion, and who thinks anyone who does not have the same beliefs is wrong. (कठोर, अतर्कसंगत विचार रखनेवाला तथा दूसरों के विचारों के प्रति असहिष्णु; हठधर्म; कट्टर; पक्षपाती)

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He was known to be a loud-mouthed, opinionated &lt;strong&gt;bigot&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mediator:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person whose job is to mediate in a disagreement. (मध्&amp;zwj;यस्&amp;zwj;थ)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diplomat:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;an official who represents his/her country in a foreign country. (विदेश में नियुक्त किसी देश का प्रतिनिधित्&amp;zwj;व करने वाला अधिकारी; राजनयज्ञ, कूटनीतिज्ञ, राजनयिक (व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति))&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mercenary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;primarily concerned with making money at the expense of ethics. (मुख्य रूप से नैतिकता की कीमत पर पैसा बनाने से संबंधित)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, one who has narrow and prejudiced religious views&amp;nbsp;is called a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Bigot.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;In my opinion, the safest food on the earth is food made by my mom.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here,&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;the safest&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;and &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;food&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;should&lt;/strong&gt; be used instead of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;safest&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;a food&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We know that&lt;strong&gt; a superlative degree &lt;/strong&gt;should be preceded by the &lt;strong&gt;definite article&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;the&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;food&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &lt;strong&gt;an uncountable noun&lt;/strong&gt; in the given context. Thus, the use of the&lt;strong&gt; infinite article&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;In my opinion,&lt;strong&gt; &lt;u&gt;the safest&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;food on the earth is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;food&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; made by my mom.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;He is an M. A. of Oxford University, London.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of &amp;quot;an&amp;quot; before &amp;quot;M. A.&amp;quot; (Master of Arts) is grammatically correct because &amp;quot;M. A.&amp;quot; begins with a vowel sound when spoken aloud (&amp;quot;em&amp;quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It correctly indicates possession or association with Oxford University, although it&amp;#39;s worth noting that Oxford University is not typically associated with London.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The association has been requesting the government to give the provision of fixing the fees since 2020.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the use of &amp;quot;have&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;has&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Association&amp;quot; is a singular noun, hence, it requires a singular verb for agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct verb phrase for the present perfect continuous tense, which is used to describe an action that began in the past and is still continuing, is &amp;quot;has been + present participle (verb-ing).&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;quot;option 2&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;RPQS.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While arranging the parts of the passage&amp;nbsp;given in options, we have to&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;find some grammatical or contextual connections between them&lt;/u&gt;, so let&amp;rsquo;s find out.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The first statement in the sequence should be the one that best connects with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;S1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It should be a continuation or extension of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;S1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;R follows&amp;nbsp;S1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because it is adding information about &lt;strong&gt;the daily routine of the grandfather.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;P follows R&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because it is adding more information about &lt;strong&gt;the grandfather&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;P must be followed by Q as it is talking about &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Nothing could detract him during that time.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is directly connected to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;S6&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as P is talking about the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Mouna Vratham ritual that&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;made him a better listener&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the sequence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;S1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;RPQSS6.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sequence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;S1 :&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(40, 40, 40); letter-spacing: -0.006px;&quot;&gt;When I was a child, my grandfather lived with me and my family.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;R :&amp;nbsp;Every morning he would wake up at the crack of dawn and sit in complete silence for an hour.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;P :&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Even as the rest of the household stirred awake and the various morning rituals unfolded around him, he stayed still and quiet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Q :&amp;nbsp;Nothing could detract him during that time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;S :&amp;nbsp;He referred to it as the Mouna Vratham, a ritual of meditative silence long practised in Indian Hindu tradition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;S6 :&amp;nbsp;He believed that abstaining from speaking for a set period each day brought him inner peace and made him a better listener.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Steps for solving Para Jumbles:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Clues include pronouns, like he, she, it, this, that, these, those; adverbs like formally, really; article a, an and the; definers like actually, finally, another; connectors like but, yet, both, also and neither nor, or, however, nevertheless.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Now, with the help of clues, try to find out qualifier and qualified sentences, so that we can make pairs of qualified and qualifier sentences to eliminate the wrong choices given in the question.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;After making pairs, start eliminating the wrong choices or options given in the question.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In case there is more than one choice, try to follow the sequence of sentences according to the occurrence of the events.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;में दिए गए गद्यांश के भागों को व्यवस्थित करते समय, हमें उनके बीच कुछ व्याकरणिक या प्रासंगिक संबंध खोजने होंगे, तो आइए जानें।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;अनुक्रम में पहला कथन वह होना चाहिए जो S1 के साथ सर्वोत्तम रूप से जुड़ता हो।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यह S1 की निरंतरता या विस्तार होना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;R, S1 का अनुसरण करता है क्योंकि यह दादाजी की दैनिक दिनचर्या के बारे में जानकारी जोड़ रहा है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;P, R का अनुसरण करता है क्योंकि यह दादा के बारे में अधिक जानकारी जोड़ रहा है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;P के बाद Q आना चाहिए क्योंकि यह इस बारे में बात कर रहा है कि &amp;quot;उस समय के दौरान कुछ भी उसे विचलित नहीं कर सकता था।&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;S, S6 से सीधे जुड़ा हुआ है क्योंकि P मौन व्रतम अनुष्ठान के बारे में बात कर रहा है जिसने उसे एक बेहतर श्रोता बना दिया।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए, अनुक्रम&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;S1RPQSS6&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;है।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;coward&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us look into the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the given options -&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;coward -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who is contemptibly lacking in the courage to do or endure dangerous or unpleasant things.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;glutton -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;an excessively greedy eater.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;miscreant -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who has done something wrong or unlawful.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;spendthrift -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who spends money in an extravagant, irresponsible way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given blank needs a word that would imply the subject lacks the courage to face challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, from the above meanings, it is clear that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;coward&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;most appropriate word for the given blank.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;He must be a &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;coward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to run away from challenges.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Adversity happens to everyone.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Among the given options, only in &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt; the spelling of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Adversity&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It means&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;difficulties or problems&amp;#39;. &lt;/strong&gt;(कठिनाइयाँ, समस्&amp;zwj;याएँ, मुसीबतें; विपत्तियाँ)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;He thinks he has come through a lot of stress and &lt;strong&gt;adversity&lt;/strong&gt; in his life.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Adversity happens to everyone.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Heritage&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heritage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: Something transmitted by or acquired from a predecessor (किसी पूर्ववर्ती द्वारा प्रेषित या प्राप्त की गई कोई चीज़&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E.g.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;-&amp;nbsp;The battlefields are part of our &lt;strong&gt;heritage&lt;/strong&gt; and should be preserved.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Heritage&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pediatrics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: The area of medicine connected with the diseases of children (चिकित्&amp;zwj;सा-शास्&amp;zwj;त्र का वह क्षेत्र जिसका संबंध बाल-रोगों से है&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;- My uncle is an expert in &lt;strong&gt;pediatrics.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;Atheism&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;: The belief that there is no God&amp;nbsp;(नास्तिकवाद)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;- He doesn&amp;#39;t embrace &lt;strong&gt;atheism.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Antique&lt;/u&gt;: Very old and therefore unusual and valuable (प्राचीनकाल की और अतएव असाधारण तथा मूल्&amp;zwj;यवान)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​​​&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E.g.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;- My brother collects&lt;strong&gt; antiques.&lt;/strong&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;blamed&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us look into the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the given options -&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;praised -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;express warm approval or admiration of.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;claimed -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;state or assert that something is the case, typically without providing evidence or proof.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;calmed -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;make (someone) tranquil and quiet; soothe.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;blamed -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;feel or declare that (someone or something) is responsible for a fault or wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence implies that in the people&amp;#39;s opinion, the sweeper was not clearing the roads.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus we can infer that the sweeper was at fault as per the people.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;blamed&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the appropriate word for the given blank.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 4&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Many people &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;blamed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the sweeper for not keeping the roads clear.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;He and I were playing&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;According to &lt;strong&gt;Syntax&lt;/strong&gt;, when &lt;strong&gt;two or more subjects &lt;/strong&gt;are connected by the conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, a &lt;strong&gt;plural verb&lt;/strong&gt; is always used in a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the sentence, &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;He and I were playing&amp;quot; there are &lt;strong&gt;two subjects &lt;/strong&gt;- &lt;strong&gt;he and I&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence they are connected with &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence,&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;He and I were playing&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; this sentence is errorless.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let us look at the error in other given sentences:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two and two makes four&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;#39;Makes&amp;#39; should be replaced with &amp;#39;make&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The Chairman with the directors are to be present: &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Are&amp;#39; should be replaced with &amp;#39;is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;If two subjects are connected with expressions like as well as, along, in addition to, with, together with, etc then the noun placed before these expressions is considered to be the main subject.&lt;br /&gt;
	Also, the verb should also be in agreement with the main subject i.e. the first subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Silver as well as gold have fallen&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;in price: &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Have&amp;#39; should be replaced with &amp;#39;has&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;RSPQ&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While arranging the parts of the sentence given in options, we have to find some grammatical or contextual connections between them, so let&amp;#39;s find out.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence should start with the subject &lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt;, &amp;#39;on the fifth morning&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence proceeds to give more information about the incident of the fifth morning when he stood on the mountain and watched the early sun in &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt; and then in &lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence further ends with &lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt; by mentioning that he watched the early sun burn off the mist that covered the forest.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Correct sentence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;on the fifth morning as I stood on the mountain&amp;nbsp;I watched the early sun burn off the mist that covered the forest.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option (4).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that can successfully invade&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the incorrect usage of the verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;invades&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The verb of a sentence depends on the subject of the sentence. If the subject is singular then the verb will be singular and if the subject is plural then the verb will be plural according to the subject-verb agreement.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;They are playing cricket.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;He is playing cricket.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is an &lt;strong&gt;antecedent&lt;/strong&gt; in the given sentence and therefore it refers to the subject of the sentence which is &amp;#39;species&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject of the sentence is plural therefore, the verb will &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;also&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;be plural i.e. &lt;strong&gt;invade&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;It is one of the few introduced species &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;that can successfully invade&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; and colonize a virgin forest.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Antecedent:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;An antecedent is a noun or pronoun to which another noun or pronoun refers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;They were laughing at my brother.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;passive voice.&lt;/strong&gt; We need to change it into &lt;strong&gt;active voice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;my brother&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;becomes the object of the active voice and the objec&lt;strong&gt;t &amp;#39;them&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;becomes the subject &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;they&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; of the active voice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;was being laughed&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;were laughing&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Structure of &lt;strong&gt;Past Continuous Tense:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice: Object + was/were + being + V3 + by + Subject.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Active Voice:&amp;nbsp; Subject + was/were + V1+ing + Object.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Correct Active Voice:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Laughing at&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;strong&gt;phrasal verb &lt;/strong&gt;which means &lt;strong&gt;to show amusement or ridicule towards someone or something.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The students were &lt;strong&gt;laughing at&lt;/strong&gt; the teacher&amp;#39;s jokes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I felt embarrassed when I realized they were &lt;strong&gt;laughing at&lt;/strong&gt; me.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: The judge said to the prisoner, &amp;quot;Do you have anything to say for yourself?&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in indirect speech and we need to convert it to direct speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we change an &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech &lt;/strong&gt;to&lt;strong&gt; direct speech&lt;/strong&gt;, we must follow these &lt;strong&gt;rules&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;asked&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;said&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb is changed according to reported speech into asking if the sentence asks for an answer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;comma (,)&lt;/strong&gt; is added after the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The first word of the direct speech is in &lt;strong&gt;capital letters&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conditional&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;if&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to an asking verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Do&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;you&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;he&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, direct speech is-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The judge said to the prisoner, &amp;quot;Do you have anything to say for yourself?&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Taru said to Kavya, &amp;quot;Will you help me in setting up my new dressing table?&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and we need to convert it to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we change an indirect speech to direct speech, we must follow these&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rules&lt;/span&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If the indirect part of the sentence use &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;asked&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; as reporting verb then a &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;question mark&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; should be added in the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The indirect speech part is always stated as a statement form. so&amp;nbsp;a &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;full stop&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; is used instead of a question tag.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;asked&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conditional &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is replaced with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted commas (&amp;quot;...&amp;quot;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma (,)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is added after the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;word of the direct speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;capital&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;letter.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The modal &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;would&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;will&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;she&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;her&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;me&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;my&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence, direct speech is -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Taru said to Kavya, &amp;quot;Will you help me in setting up my new dressing table?&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I said to carpenter, &amp;quot;How long will you take to polish my furniture?&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and we need to convert it to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we change an indirect speech to direct speech, we must follow these&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rules&lt;/span&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If the indirect part of the sentence use &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;asked&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; as reporting verb then a &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;question mark&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; should be added in the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The indirect speech part is always stated as a statement form. so&amp;nbsp;a &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;full stop&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; is used instead of a question tag.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;asked&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;said to&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The question part should be in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted commas (&amp;quot;...&amp;quot;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma (,)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is added after the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;word of the direct speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;capital&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;letter.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The modal &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;would&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;will&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;he&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence, direct speech is -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I said to carpenter, &amp;quot;How long will you take to polish my furniture?&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;The teacher said to me, &amp;quot;Why did you reach the examination hall so late?&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;As per the question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Asked&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;said to&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;because the given question is an example of an&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;interrogative&amp;nbsp;sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a question word.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Commas and inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;had reached&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;did reach&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;. Because in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Direct to Indirect&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;transformation&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;simple past&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;tense is changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;past perfect tense&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;you&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;because in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;transformation&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first-person pronoun&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is changed according to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting verb.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Why&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;will be used as a &lt;strong&gt;conjunction&lt;/strong&gt; because we know that in &lt;strong&gt;an&amp;nbsp;interrogative sentence&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;strong&gt;a question word,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the question word itself is used as a conjunction.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;The teacher said to me, &amp;quot;Why did you reach the examination hall so late?&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The newsreader said, &amp;ldquo;I am here for a heartfelt apology for making such a comment.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 1 is the correct Indirect Speech because it accurately reports what the newsreader said in the past tense without changing the meaning of the sentence. The verb &amp;quot;&amp;quot;was&amp;quot;&amp;quot; is changed to &amp;quot;&amp;quot;am&amp;quot;&amp;quot; to reflect the present tense in direct speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 2 is incorrect because it changes the tense of the sentence to present continuous, which is not what the newsreader said.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 3 is incorrect because it changes the tense to present perfect, which is also not what the newsreader said.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 4 is incorrect because it changes the tense to past tense, which is not what the newsreader said.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The newsreader said, &amp;ldquo;I am here for a heartfelt apology for making such a comment.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 3&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The sentence&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;The thief asked if he remembered the place where they had hidden their jewellery&amp;quot; is a&lt;strong&gt; reported speech,&lt;/strong&gt; and the goal here is to &lt;strong&gt;change it back &lt;/strong&gt;into direct speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When transforming&lt;/strong&gt; reported speech back into direct speech,&lt;strong&gt; we need to change the tense back&lt;/strong&gt; to its original form.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;remember&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;remains the same as it&amp;#39;s a mental verb which doesn&amp;#39;t usually change in reported speech.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the original sentence,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;had hidden&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is in the &lt;strong&gt;past perfect tense,&lt;/strong&gt; which usually transforms back into present perfect in direct speech, thus &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;have hidden&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the &lt;strong&gt;correct tense &lt;/strong&gt;to use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The thief asked, &amp;ldquo;Do you remember the place where we have hidden our jewellery?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;ZXY&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence states that the hare laughs at the idea, but &amp;quot;which idea?&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us explore the labelled&amp;nbsp;sentences:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In sentence Z &amp;quot;that&amp;quot; is used as a relative pronoun&lt;/strong&gt; to introduce an adjective clause; &lt;strong&gt;used to describe more about the noun &amp;quot;the idea&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In sentence X, we can see the use of &amp;quot;comma&amp;quot; which indicates a smaller break &lt;/strong&gt;also the use of &amp;quot;but&amp;quot; indicates the introduction of a contradictory clause.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The sentence Y has a conclusive tone to it&lt;/strong&gt;, hence, it can be used as the final sentence in the given arrangement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the completed paragraph will be in the following manner:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The hare laughs at the idea that a tortoise could run faster than him, but when the two actually race, the results are surprising.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer is option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1) i.e. &amp;quot;ADCEBF.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the abovementioned paragraph, there is a chronological sequence of the sentences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;the first sentence as per the given instructions. It begins with the noun &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Raja Rammohan Roy&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;who was the pioneer of women&amp;rsquo;s rights in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the second sentence&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;as&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;it mentions the reason why&amp;nbsp;Raja Rammohan Roy is known as the pioneer of women&amp;rsquo;s rights in India.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the third sentence as it&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;explains the background of the situation and what Raja&amp;nbsp;Rammohan Roy did in the past years for women&amp;#39;s rights.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence E&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the fourth&amp;nbsp;sentence as it&amp;nbsp;mentions another view that his writings focused on.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the fifth sentence as it&amp;nbsp;further tells about his writings and his&amp;nbsp;interpretation of Hindu scriptures.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence&amp;nbsp;F&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the last sentence as per the given instructions. It tells that he urged the British government to abolish Sati.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct arrangement is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ADCEBF.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The correct order is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;A. Raja Rammohan Roy is known as the pioneer of women&amp;rsquo;s rights in India.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;D. The reason behind this is specifically his support for the abolition of Sati.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;C. Since 1818, Roy wrote in great detail about Sati and how he was pro-abolition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;E. His writing, however, also focused on reading and interpretation of scriptures.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;B. Roy argued that Hindu scriptures did not condone or encourage Sati.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;F. His views resonated with the British argument that widows were coerced into the pyre for material gains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;option 2) i.e. &amp;quot;AEDCBF.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the abovementioned paragraph, there is a chronological sequence of the sentences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the first sentence as per the given instructions. It begins with the noun &amp;#39;discipline&amp;#39; and describes it can not be imposed forcefully.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence E&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the second sentence&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;as it further explains the above-mentioned point&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence D&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the third sentence.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;It&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;defines the above-mentioned points as&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;self-discipline&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence C&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the fourth&amp;nbsp;sentence as it describes the contrary part that fear or punishment are futile tools to make someone disciplined.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence B&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the fifth sentence as&amp;nbsp;it mentions the reason why discipline cannot be forced.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sentence F&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the last sentence as per the given instructions. It&amp;nbsp;describes that to teach someone discipline a teacher needs to act with love and affection.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct arrangement is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;AEDCBF.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The correct order is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;. Discipline is not a thing to be thrust upon our boys and girls from outside.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;. It must come automatically from the core of their heart.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt;. This type of discipline is called self-discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;. It is not at all based on fear or punishment as forced discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;. On the contrary, it is purely based on their conscience.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;F&lt;/strong&gt;. It should be controlled by the love and affection of the teachers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The teacher said that honesty is the best policy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The teacher said that honesty was the best policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is grammatically incorrect in this sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct usage is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The teacher said that honesty is the best policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;instead of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The teacher said that honesty was the best policy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in the &lt;strong&gt;Reported speech &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; universal truth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the reported clause is a universal truth or any historical event or habitual action, then the tense of the indirect speech doesn&amp;rsquo;t change, no matter in whatever tense the reporting verb is.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The teacher said that honesty is the best policy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in direct speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb of the sentence is in past tense.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore the tense of the reported speech will be changed accordingly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Present Continuous Tense changes to Past Continuous Tense.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The interrogative sentence changes to a simple sentence in an indirect speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, helping verb will not be placed before the subject.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Conjunction &lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt; is not used in conversion interrogative sentence as wh-word acts as conjunction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;She asked me what I was doing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hint-text-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hint&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 1 and 2 cannot be our answers as helping verb is placed before the subject of the reported speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;To rely on someone or something for success&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given word.&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hitch one&amp;#39;s wagon to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;to attempt to benefit from something or someone else&amp;#39;s success or potential by closely associating with it or them&amp;nbsp;(&lt;strong&gt;किसी वस्तु या किसी ओर&amp;nbsp;की सफलता या क्षमता से उसके या उनके साथ निकटता से जुड़कर लाभ उठाने का प्रयास करना&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The agencies responsible for macroeconomic policy have&lt;strong&gt; hitched their wagon to&lt;/strong&gt; Anglo-American economics.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​From the above lines, we can say that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;To rely on someone or something for success&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct meaning of the given idiom/phrase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​​​​​​Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;o&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ption 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;She said, &amp;quot;I stay in a hostel.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Given sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;She said that she stays in a hostel&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Simple Present Tense&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and in &lt;strong&gt;Indirect&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;b&gt;speech&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The rule for changing a &lt;strong&gt;Simple Present Indefinite tense&lt;/strong&gt; form into an &lt;strong&gt;Direct Speech&lt;/strong&gt; is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;That&lt;/strong&gt; is replaced with &lt;strong&gt;inverted&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;commas&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tense&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence &lt;strong&gt;remains the same.&lt;/strong&gt; In the given sentence, Simple Present Tense will remain same while converting into Direct Speech.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure&lt;/strong&gt;: Subject + Inverted commas + Object. (Direct Speech)
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;She says, &amp;quot;She lives in the New Delhi.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure&lt;/strong&gt;: Subject + That + Object. (Indirect Speech)
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;She said that she lived in the New Delhi.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;She said, &amp;quot;I stay in a hostel.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct speech&lt;/strong&gt; is used to describe what someone has stated. When we just repeat someone else&amp;#39;s words, enclosing the phrase in speech marks, we are using direct speaking.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;used to report what someone said without speech bubbles and without necessarily using their exact words. It is also called reported speech.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Vikash said, &amp;ldquo;I shall leave for Mumbai tomorrow.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech,&lt;/strong&gt; and we need to convert it to &lt;strong&gt;direct speech&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we change an &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech &lt;/strong&gt;to &lt;strong&gt;direct speech&lt;/strong&gt;, we must follow these &lt;strong&gt;rules&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;said&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; remains unchanged.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is replaced with &lt;strong&gt;inverted commas (&amp;quot;...&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt; to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;comma (,)&lt;/strong&gt; is added after the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; first word of the direct speech&lt;/strong&gt; is in &lt;strong&gt;capital letters&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;next day&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;tomorrow&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The modal&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;would&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;shall&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;he&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, direct speech is -&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Vikash said, &amp;ldquo;I shall leave for Mumbai tomorrow.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The student said, &amp;quot;I must study hard for the upcoming exam.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech,&lt;/strong&gt; and we need to convert it to &lt;strong&gt;direct speech.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we change an &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;direct speech&lt;/strong&gt;, we must follow these &lt;strong&gt;rules:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;said&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; remains unchanged.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The conjunction &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;that&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is replaced with &lt;strong&gt;inverted commas (&amp;quot;...&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt; to show the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;comma (,)&lt;/strong&gt; is added after the direct speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The first word of the direct speech is in &lt;strong&gt;capital letters&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;had to&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; changes to&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;must&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; in direct speech.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;he&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; changes to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;I&amp;#39;.&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For converting &lt;strong&gt;direct speech &lt;/strong&gt;into &lt;strong&gt;indirect speech&lt;/strong&gt;, the present modals (e.g., Can, May, Must) are changed into past modals (e.g., Could, Might, Had to).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, direct speech is-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The student said, &amp;quot;I must study hard for the upcoming exam.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The hostel warden told the inspector that Rahul had&amp;nbsp;arrived on Sunday from the holiday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the reporting speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Simple Past Tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;then all the speech&amp;nbsp;Changes&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to&amp;nbsp;Past Perfect tense.&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Arrived&amp;nbsp;----- Had arrived&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Said to&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the reporting verb changed into&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;told.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Replace&amp;nbsp;comma (,) and inverted commas (&amp;quot; &amp;quot;)&amp;nbsp;with the conjunction &amp;#39;that&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The third person(Rohit)&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;reporting speech&amp;nbsp;remains unchanged.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​Thus, the final sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The hostel warden told the inspector that Rahul had&amp;nbsp;arrived on Sunday from the holiday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;What is Direct &amp;amp; Indirect Speech?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Direct speech&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; reporting the message of the speaker in the exact words as spoken by him.&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Direct speech example&lt;/span&gt;: Anjali said, &amp;quot;I am writing now&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;: reporting the message of the speaker in our own words&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; user-select: text !important;&quot;&gt;Indirect speech example&lt;/span&gt;: Anjali said that she was writing then.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is-&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Peak.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Words like&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;peek&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;peak&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;pick&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;pique&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;are called homophones.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This means that they sound the same but have different spellings and meanings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the &lt;strong&gt;meanings &lt;/strong&gt;of the&amp;nbsp;words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peek:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;to look at something quickly and secretly because you should not be looking at it. (किसी व्&amp;zwj;यक्ति या घटना को एक क्षण के लिए तथा छिप कर देखना (विशेषतः जब इस प्रकार देखना अनुचित है))&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peak:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;the point at which something is the highest, best, strongest, etc. (वह बिंदु जहाँ कोई वस्&amp;zwj;तु उच्&amp;zwj;चतम, सर्वोत्तम, प्रबलतम आदि स्थिति में हो)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pick:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;to choose somebody/something from a group of people or things. ((व्&amp;zwj;यक्तियों या वस्&amp;zwj;तुओं के समूह में से) चुनना, चयन करना, छाँटना)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pique:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;arouse (interest or curiosity).&amp;nbsp;(जगाना (रुचि या जिज्ञासा))&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence talks about&amp;nbsp;August marking the highest month for prices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The option&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Peak&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is correct in this context.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Prices reach a &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;peak&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; during August.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;Sometimes&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given idiom:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Now and then-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;occasionally

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example: &lt;/span&gt;We visit to our uncle&amp;#39;s house &lt;strong&gt;now and then&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sometimes is similar to occasionally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;option 3&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Meanings in Hindi:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Now and then-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;कभी-कभी

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;We visit to our uncle&amp;#39;s house&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;now and then&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Present Perfect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Present Perfect&lt;/strong&gt; tense is a verb tense which is primarily used to express &lt;em&gt;an action that took place at some indefinite time in the past&lt;/em&gt;. The present perfect tense can also be used to express &lt;em&gt;an action that began in the past and continues now.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verb structure Present Perfect tense aspect usually follows is: &lt;strong&gt;has/have&lt;/strong&gt; (depending on the subject) + &lt;strong&gt;Past Participle form of the verb&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;He and his wife &lt;u&gt;have travelled&lt;/u&gt; all over the world&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example, &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;My dog &lt;u&gt;has stolen&lt;/u&gt; the cat&amp;rsquo;s food&lt;/em&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence follows the structure of the Present Perfect verb structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tense &lt;/strong&gt;indicates the time at which an action takes place. In English, we usually speak of tense as representing &lt;strong&gt;past&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;present&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;future&lt;/strong&gt; times. Each of these tenses is further divided into four aspects such as &lt;strong&gt;Simple, Continuous, Perfect &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Perfect Continuous&lt;/strong&gt;, depending on &lt;span&gt;how an action, event, or state, denoted by a verb, extends over time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;A mistake made in something you are trying to achieve.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Only&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;follows a sentence structure i.e. is a complete sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 is incorrect&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;as a verb is missing after &amp;#39;A dog&amp;#39;. The correct sentence should be:&amp;nbsp;A dog&lt;strong&gt; is&lt;/strong&gt; barking up the tree.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Option 3&amp;nbsp;is incorrect&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;subject is missing here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct sentence should be:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;I am/You are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;talking to the wrong person.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Option 4&amp;nbsp;is incorrect&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;subject is missing here.&amp;nbsp;The correct sentence should be:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;You are/He is/She is&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;yelling too much&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Thus, the only possible correct sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;A mistake made in something you are trying to achieve.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Present Continuous&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;Present Continuous tense.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;we use the&lt;strong&gt; Present continuous&lt;/strong&gt; for things that are happening at the moment of speaking.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the Present continuous tense is: &lt;strong&gt;Subject + am/is/are + present participle (verb+ing) + Object&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example -&lt;em&gt; Boys are playing cricket.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;Present Continuous tense.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option (3).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;had increased&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, we use the &lt;strong&gt;past perfect &lt;/strong&gt;with the &lt;strong&gt;past simple&lt;/strong&gt; as we are talking about two actions or events in the past.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;We always use the &lt;strong&gt;past perfec&lt;/strong&gt;t for the action that happened first.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;We can link the&lt;strong&gt; two actions &lt;/strong&gt;using a time expression.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;After using the &lt;strong&gt;past perfect&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;1st part&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence, we use &lt;strong&gt;simple past&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;2nd part &lt;/strong&gt;of the sentence.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;For example:-&amp;nbsp; &lt;em&gt;After&amp;nbsp;she &lt;strong&gt;had &lt;/strong&gt;read all the greetings cards, she &lt;strong&gt;made &lt;/strong&gt;a short thank-you speech.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​​Therefore, the correct answer is Option 4.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Correct sentence&amp;nbsp; -&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;She&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt; had increased&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; the speed of the car before we came to a sharp bend in the road.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simple past tense:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The simple past tense shows that you are talking about something that has already happened.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Subject + V2 + Object + time phrase.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example:- &lt;em&gt;Lisa &lt;strong&gt;went &lt;/strong&gt;to the supermarket yesterday.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Past perfect tense:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The past perfect, also called the pluperfect, is a verb tense used to talk about actions that were completed before some point in the past.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;​Structure:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Subject + had + V3 + Object.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For example:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Daniel &lt;strong&gt;had left &lt;/strong&gt;by the time Erica got to his house.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Here, the erroneous part&amp;nbsp;is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;such a map.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part (such a map)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the phrase&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;such a&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is one of this or that kind : one of a specified or understood kind.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;i&gt;She is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;such a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; liar.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;only&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;used to show that there is a single one or very few of something, or that there are no others.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;I was the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; person on the train.​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, we need to remove&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;such a&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;from the sentence to make it grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;It is rare because it is the only map available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;ACBD.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct order to form a meaningful and coherent paragraph is&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A- The average person has about one to one and a half gallons of liquid&amp;nbsp;inside his or her body called blood.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;C- Blood is the most essential and important part of the body&amp;#39;s circulatory system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;B- The circulatory system is responsible&amp;nbsp;for the movement of blood throughout the body through blood vessels.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;D- The heart is the pump that makes it all happen.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_10920C&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is correct option.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;consolidate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Consolidate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;make (something) physically stronger or more solid.

