		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sojourn &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rArr; A &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;temporary stay.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Idiosyncrasy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span&gt;A unusual mode of behaviour or way of thought peculiar to an individual.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above reference, it can be concluded that &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Exodus&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the correct word to substitute for the given description.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The original term &amp;#39;exodus&amp;#39; &lt;span&gt;describes the departure of the Israelites from Egypt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1 &lt;/strong&gt;i.e. &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;i - b, ii - d, iii - c, iv - a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the meanings of the terms in the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;broke out&amp;#39; is past tense of &amp;#39;break out.&amp;#39; It is usually used with diseases and wars and it means &lt;strong&gt;to suddenly begin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. It matches the description &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;began suddenly in a violent way&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;In accordance with&amp;#39; is a phrase used to mean &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;in a manner conforming with&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. It matches the description &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;according to a particular rule, principle or system&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;A helping hand&amp;#39; is a common phrase used to refer to &lt;strong&gt;help&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;It matches the word &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;assistance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Can not stomach&amp;#39; is a common idiom that has two different meanings:
		&lt;ol&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ILfuVd&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hgKElc&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;To be unable to muster the courage, determination, or resolve to do, face, or experience something unpleasant&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ILfuVd&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hgKElc&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;To not to be able to tolerate someone or something&lt;/b&gt;. This one matches the description &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;was not able to tolerate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ol&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above discussion, we can see that the correct combination of matching is &lt;strong&gt;i - b, ii - d, iii - c, iv - a&lt;/strong&gt;, which is given in &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;​&lt;/span&gt;These days most people are using email instead of writing letters&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;this sentence, we are talking about the continuous use of&amp;nbsp;email instead of written letters.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, we need to write the sentence in the&lt;strong&gt; Present Continuous Tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;present continuous tense&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used to describe dynamic actions that happen repeatedly, are currently happening, or will be happening in the near future.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Structure:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + is/am/are + V1 + ing + object.&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Boys are playing cricket in the garden area.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Two rules are applicable in this sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rule 1:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The subject &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;most people&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is a plural subject, so we need a plural helping verb &lt;strong&gt;(are) &lt;/strong&gt;with it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rule 2:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The first part of the sentence is in the Present Continuous Tense, so the second part must be in the same tense to maintain the uniformity of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;These days most people are using email instead of writing letters.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct solution is&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &amp;#39;have been searching&amp;#39;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the above sentence, in order to pick the correct tense to fill in the blank, we first have to identify the tense of the rest of the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the end of the sentence, we find the word &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;since&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt; which is used to denote &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;the period between the time mentioned and the time under consideration&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So this makes the sentence a &lt;em&gt;present perfect continuous tense&lt;/em&gt;,which is used to denote that an action has started in the recent past and is still continuing in the present.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of a present perfect continuous tense is &lt;em&gt;Subject+ has/have + been+ present participle+ing+ rest of the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So the correct option will be &amp;#39;have been searching&amp;#39; making the sentence&lt;em&gt; &amp;#39;I have been searching for this book since Monday&amp;#39;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;disorder&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The underlined word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;fiasco&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;a complete failure, especially a ludicrous or humiliating one.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Synonyms are&amp;nbsp;failure, disaster, catastrophe, debacle, shambles, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:-&amp;nbsp;His plans turned into a &lt;strong&gt;fiasco.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&amp;#39;disorder&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;a state of confusion.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Synonyms are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;mess, disarray, disorganization,&amp;nbsp;etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​Hence&lt;strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;correct &amp;#39;synonym&amp;#39; for the underlined word from the option given is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;disorder&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;gaiety:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;the state or quality of being light-hearted or cheerful.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;entertainment:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;the action of providing or being provided with amusement or enjoyment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rejoicing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;great joy; jubilation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;prosaic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Humdrum&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;lacking excitement or variety; boringly monotonous.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Humdrum&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; शब्द का अर्थ है उत्साह या विविधता की कमी; उबाऊ; नीरस।)&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Most of the work is fairly &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;humdrum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meanings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Cunning:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;clever in a dishonest or bad way. (चालाक, धूर्त)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Patriotic:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;having or showing great love for your country. (देशभक्ति पूर्ण; राष्&amp;zwj;ट्रप्रेम से युक्त)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Prosaic:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;without interest, imagination, and excitement. (रुचि, कल्पना और उत्साह के बिना​।)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Poetic:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;connected with poets or like a poem. (कवि-विषयक या कविता के सदृश या काव्&amp;zwj;योचित)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meanings&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given words, we can say that the synonym of the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;humdrum&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; that is mentioned in bold is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;prosaic.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;SRQP&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first sentence which is fixed introduces the need for the crop in Europe and the revenue that could be produced by the British Company.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence S states the British Company was trying to expand the cultivation of opium and indigo(the 1st sentence introduces the crops)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence R states after some time, the British forced cultivators to produce other crops(other than indigo)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence Q states the name of the other crops.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence P states that the British used a variety of methods to expand the cultivation(of the crops mentioned above)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence the correct passage:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt;: The British also realised that the countryside could not only yield revenue, it could also grow the crops that Europe required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;S:&lt;/strong&gt; By the late eighteenth century the Company was trying its best to expand the cultivation of opium and indigo.&lt;strong&gt;R: &lt;/strong&gt;In the century and a half that followed, the British persuaded or forced cultivators in various parts of India to produce other crops:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Q:&lt;/strong&gt; jute in Bengal, tea in Assam, sugarcane in the United Provinces (now Uttar Pradesh), cotton in Maharashtra and Punjab, rice in Madras.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;P: &lt;/strong&gt;The British used a variety of methods to expand the cultivation of crops that they needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;S6:&lt;/strong&gt; But this expansion of cultivation was not beneficial.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;SQRP&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

