	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the &lt;strong&gt;Present Continuous Tense -&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​Subject + Is/am/are + Verb (ing Form) + Object&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​​&lt;/strong&gt;Eg. He is playing a game.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; shows the sentence correctly in the &lt;strong&gt;Present Continuous Tense&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
