	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;The office staff safely locked the question papers printed by the departments for the examinations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in passive voice, which means the subject (the question papers) is acted upon by the verb (were safely locked). In order to convert this sentence into active voice, we need to make the subject (the question papers) the doer of the action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In option 2, the subject is &amp;quot;the departments,&amp;quot; which is not correct because the departments are not the ones who locked the question papers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In option 3, the subject is &amp;quot;the departments,&amp;quot; which is correct for the action of printing the question papers, but the rest of the sentence does not accurately convey the information given in the original sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 1 also does not convey the information in the original sentence accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 4 accurately conveys the information in the original sentence in active voice, with the subject (the office staff) performing the action (locking the question papers).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, &lt;strong&gt;option 4 is the correct answer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;SQRP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

