&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;The correct passage&amp;nbsp;is&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Human evolution is intimately related to the origin of life and its development on the face of the earth. &lt;strong&gt;S.&lt;/strong&gt; The term evolution was first applied by the English philosopher Herbert Spencer to mean the historical development of life. &lt;strong&gt;Q. &lt;/strong&gt;Since then evolution denotes a change, although the term may be defined in several ways.&lt;strong&gt; R. &lt;/strong&gt;In the context of man, biological evolution started with the &amp;lsquo;Origin of life&amp;rsquo;. &lt;strong&gt;P.&lt;/strong&gt; The first successful formation of protoplasm initiated life and its continuous development proceeded towards complexity to give rise to different life forms of evolved types. &lt;strong&gt;S6.&lt;/strong&gt; Philosophers, Thinkers, and Scientists all submitted their varied thought and propositions regarding the nature and mechanism of the origin of life on earth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is an error in &lt;strong&gt;part (a)&lt;/strong&gt;. The correct &lt;strong&gt;phrase&lt;/strong&gt; should be: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;As the world becomes more connected through the internet&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;through&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; should be used instead of &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;threw&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; because &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;through&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;by means of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;via&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; which fits the meaning of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;threw&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is a &lt;strong&gt;past tense form&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;throw&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; which means &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to toss or hurl&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and it does not fit the meaning of the sentence in this context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As the world becomes more connected through&amp;nbsp;the internet&lt;/strong&gt;, the importance of cybersecurity has grown exponentially.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;heard of.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the meanings of the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Heard of:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;be aware of or know of the existence of someone or something.&amp;nbsp;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example - Nobody had ever &lt;strong&gt;heard of &lt;/strong&gt;my college.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Heard from:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;If you hear from someone, you get a letter, email, or phone call from that person, or that person tells you something.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Heard through:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;to listen to all of something. (सब कुछ सुन&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Heard over:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Incorrect construction&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence implies that whether the person was aware of the&amp;nbsp;Aurora Islands.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 1&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;Have you &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;heard of&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the Aurora Islands?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;dinner served with care&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 &amp;quot;dinner served with care&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; correctly rearranges the given jumbled words and fills in the blank&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct order of the words is: &lt;strong&gt;subject, verb, adverb, preposition&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;dinner&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; the &lt;strong&gt;verb&lt;/strong&gt; is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;served&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; the &lt;strong&gt;adverb&lt;/strong&gt; is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;with&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; and the &lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt; is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;care&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;dinner served with care&lt;/strong&gt; was delicious.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;They had came a long way.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in the format: &amp;quot;Subject+ have+ root form of the verb &amp;quot;come&amp;quot; + rest of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the given sentence is in present perfect tense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now, we are required to change the given sentence to past perfect tense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;past perfect, also&amp;nbsp;called the pluperfect, is a verb tense used to talk about actions that were completed before some point in the past.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; formula for the past perfect tense is&amp;nbsp;had + [past participle]&lt;/strong&gt;. It doesn&amp;rsquo;t matter if the subject is singular or plural; the formula doesn&amp;rsquo;t change.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: They had used all the washable paint.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now, among the given options:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The sentence in option 3 is constructed in the pattern: subject+ had+ past participle of the verb &amp;quot;come&amp;quot;+ rest of the sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the given sentence in past perfect tense will be read as:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They had came a long way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;the correct answer is option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;cautious&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The term &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;cautious&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; generally describes a quality of being careful to avoid potential problems or dangers. &lt;strong&gt;(सतर्क)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It implies a sense of awareness and mindfulness towards something that could potentially cause harm.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: Given the fire safety accidents that had happened in the past, the company was very&lt;strong&gt; cautious &lt;/strong&gt;while planning their new housing units.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given context means that the subject&amp;nbsp;is careful and mindful while discussing her past, probably because it might contain painful memories or experiences she does not want to accidentally reveal or aggravate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gracious&lt;/strong&gt;: Exhibiting kindness, courtesy, or charm.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(दयालु)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dignified&lt;/strong&gt;: Showing a composed or serious manner that is worthy of respect.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;(गरिमामय)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turbulent&lt;/strong&gt;: Characterized by conflict, disorder, or confusion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(अशांत)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(b)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;in the&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect in the given sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;With the verb &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;came&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, the correct preposition is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;into&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; when indicating movement toward the inside of a place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;came in the class&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; should be replaced with &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;came into the class&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Options (a), (c), and (d)&lt;/strong&gt; are grammatically correct in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;He came &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;into the&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; class without the teacher&amp;#39;s permission.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come in&lt;/strong&gt; means to enter generally, but when followed directly by a noun/place, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;into&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is preferred.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Example: She came &lt;strong&gt;into the room&lt;/strong&gt; quietly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Example: Please &lt;strong&gt;come in&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct active voice for the given sentence is: &lt;strong&gt;Someone has completed the task.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The original sentence is in the &lt;strong&gt;passive voice,&lt;/strong&gt; where the focus is on the task and not on who completed it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the&lt;strong&gt; passive voice&lt;/strong&gt;, the subject is often not specified, and the focus is on the action or the object of the action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To convert a passive voice sentence to an active voice sentence, we need to follow certain rules:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Identify the subject and object in the passive sentence. In this case, the subject is not specified, and the object is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the task.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Rewrite the sentence to make the subject the doer of the action and the object the receiver of the action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this case, we need to add a subject (the person or group of people who completed the task) and make it the doer of the action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We also need to make the task the receiver of the action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Based on these rules, &lt;strong&gt;option 1) Someone has completed the task&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct active voice for the given sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2) Someone has been completing the task&lt;/strong&gt; is incorrect because it implies ongoing or continuous action, rather than a completed action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3) Someone will be completing the task&lt;/strong&gt; is also incorrect because it refers to a future action, rather than a completed action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4) Someone completes the task &lt;/strong&gt;is not a correct option because it refers to the task&amp;#39;s completion as a general statement and not a specific instance of the task being completed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;spectators&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Spectators&amp;#39; is the correct term to refer to people who are watching a game or event in a stadium. For example, The football match attracted thousands of spectators.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Herd&amp;#39; refers to a large group of animals, especially hoofed mammals, that live, feed, or migrate together. It is not appropriate in this context.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Audience&amp;#39; refers to the assembled spectators or listeners at a public event, such as a play, movie, concert, or meeting. It is not the best choice for a sports event in a stadium.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Crowd&amp;#39; is a large number of people gathered together, typically in a disorganized or unruly way. It does not specifically refer to people watching a game or event.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The option that is opposite in meaning to the underlined word &amp;quot;exponential&amp;quot; is: &lt;strong&gt;meager&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;exponential&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; refers to rapid or significant growth or increase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the opposite of exponential would be something that signifies limited or insufficient growth, which is represented by the word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;meager&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now let&amp;#39;s explain the other options:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;aggressive&lt;/strong&gt;: This word does not convey the opposite meaning of &amp;quot;exponential.&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Aggressive&amp;quot; refers to a forceful or assertive behavior, which is unrelated to the concept of growth or development.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rampant&lt;/strong&gt;: This word does not convey the opposite meaning of &amp;quot;exponential.&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Rampant&amp;quot; refers to something widespread or unrestrained, which is not the opposite of rapid growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;augmented&lt;/strong&gt;: This word does not convey the opposite meaning of &amp;quot;exponential.&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Augmented&amp;quot; means to increase or enhance something, which is similar to the idea of growth but does not represent the opposite meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct option for the opposite meaning of &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;exponential&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is 3) &lt;strong&gt;meager&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct order is: &lt;strong&gt;RPQS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The paragraph revolves around Helen Keller and her inspiring life story.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence R&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Helen Keller is surely an inspiration to everyone.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This serves as a broad, introductory statement, presenting Helen Keller as an inspirational figure. It sets the overall tone for the paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence P&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;The story of My Life is full of stories of her sheer hard work and perseverance.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This sentence follows up the first statement by giving an insight into Helen&amp;#39;s life, touching upon her hard work and perseverance, which could be part of the reasons why she&amp;#39;s inspirational.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence Q&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Her teacher played a huge role in her life.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This statement provides additional context to the narrative. It makes sense to mention it after talking about her life in general, focusing on an important person who had significant impact on her &amp;mdash; her teacher.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence S&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Mark Twain was right when he said that Helen Keller was one of the greatest characters of the 19th century.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This sentence concludes the paragraph by echoing the sentiment presented in the opening sentence and reinforcing the point of Helen Keller being an inspirational figure, this time backed by a quotation from a renowned author, Mark Twain.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This sequence forms a coherent narrative, progressing from a general statement about Helen Keller&amp;#39;s inspirational status, going into more specifics about her life and the important people in it, and finally ending with a validating quote from Mark Twain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;of&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The preposition &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used to show possession or belonging.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the context of the sentence, the photographs belong to &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;their baby&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;, thus &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the most suitable preposition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence aims to convey that &lt;strong&gt;the photographs depict their baby, making &amp;#39;of&amp;#39; the correct choice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In English grammar, when showing what a picture is about, we use &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 1 (&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;to&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;) would indicate direction, which doesn&amp;rsquo;t fit here.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 2 (&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;on&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;) would suggest that the photographs are located on top of the baby, which doesn&amp;rsquo;t make sense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 4 (&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;for&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;) would imply that the photographs were intended for the baby, which is not the intended meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;The farmers of this village grow paddy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Voice&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Simple Present tense.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the given question, we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active&amp;nbsp;Voice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The structure of the given sentence is as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject (objective case)+ is/am/were + V3 + Object (subjective case).&amp;nbsp;(Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + V1(s/es)+ Object. (Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;They are shown some rare photographs by their cousin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(Passive Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Their cousin shows them some rare photographs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;(Active Voice)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The subject&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Paddy&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the object&amp;nbsp;is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;the farmers.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The subject&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be put in place of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the object&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be put in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Is grown&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Grow.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 2.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The farmers of this village grow paddy.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 4 i.e. &lt;strong&gt;1, 4, 3, 2.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Sentence (1) introduces Lakshadweep by describing its geographical location.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Sentence (4) then provides more specific details about the structure of Lakshadweep, describing its main islands and geographical features.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
