	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Relation:&lt;/strong&gt; The phrase &amp;quot;in relation to&amp;quot; means &amp;quot;in connection with&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;concerning.&amp;quot; This perfectly fits the context, as the winners and losers are identified in connection to specific economic sectors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Narration:&lt;/strong&gt; This refers to the act of telling a story. It is grammatically and contextually incorrect here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Objection:&lt;/strong&gt; This means an expression or feeling of disapproval or opposition. It does not fit the context of describing how winners and losers are distributed across sectors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) Anticipation:&lt;/strong&gt; This means the action of looking forward to something. It is irrelevant to the distribution of winners and losers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, &amp;quot;relation&amp;quot; is the most appropriate word for blank no. 2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Complete Passage: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Scholars have long noted that International Monetary Fund (IMF) restructuring programmes (1) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; winners and losers, but always in (2) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;relation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; to different sectors of the economy. For example, the fact that programmes (3) &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;____&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;to strengthen exports has been shown to favour farmers and business owners over urban middle class state employees like civil servants. The problem with purely (4) &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;____&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;analyses is highlighted when you look at citizens&amp;rsquo; experiences. One (5) &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;____&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;of the survey data, covering nine countries in Africa, showed that three out of ten civil servants actually thought IMF reforms made their lives better.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

