		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Compelling:&lt;/strong&gt; This means evoking interest or admiration, or forcing something to happen. It does not fit the context of describing sectors in an economic analysis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) Compiling:&lt;/strong&gt; This means gathering or collecting information. While data is compiled, &amp;quot;compiling sectors&amp;quot; is not a meaningful phrase in this context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Given the options, &amp;quot;comparing&amp;quot; is the most appropriate choice, implying that a purely comparative analysis of sectors is insufficient to understand citizens&amp;#39; experiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
