&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence refers to &amp;quot;One (5)_____________________ of the survey data, covering nine countries in Africa, showed that three out of ten civil servants actually thought IMF reforms made their lives better.&amp;quot; This implies a specific part or a distinct portion of the survey data that revealed a particular outcome or observation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s examine the options:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Ligament:&lt;/strong&gt; A band of fibrous tissue in the body. This is irrelevant to survey data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) Payment:&lt;/strong&gt; The act of paying money. This is irrelevant to survey data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3) Segment:&lt;/strong&gt; A part of something. This fits the context well, referring to a distinct portion or section of the overall survey data. For example, a segment of the data might focus on civil servants&amp;#39; opinions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) Fragment:&lt;/strong&gt; A small part broken or separated off something. While it means a part, &amp;quot;fragment&amp;quot; often implies incompleteness or being broken. &amp;quot;Segment&amp;quot; is a more neutral term for a distinct part of a whole, which is more appropriate for discussing survey data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, &amp;quot;segment&amp;quot; is the most appropriate word for blank no. 5, indicating a specific portion or aspect of the survey data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Complete Passage: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Scholars have long noted that International Monetary Fund (IMF) restructuring programmes (1) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; winners and losers, but always in (2) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;relation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; to different sectors of the economy. For example, the fact that programmes (3) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;attempt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; to strengthen exports has been shown to favour farmers and business owners over urban middle class state employees like civil servants. The problem with purely (4) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;sectoral&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; analyses is highlighted when you look at citizens&amp;rsquo; experiences. One (5) &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;segment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; of the survey data, covering nine countries in Africa, showed that three out of ten civil servants actually thought IMF reforms made their lives better.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;on&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The verb &amp;quot;focused&amp;quot; typically takes the preposition &amp;quot;on&amp;quot; when referring to the object or area of attention.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In this context, the artists directed their attention or efforts &amp;quot;on&amp;quot; depicting the beauty of the human form and nature.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Focused on&amp;quot; means to give all your attention or effort to something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Complete Passage: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;During the Renaissance, artists focused 1. &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; depicting the beauty of the human form and nature. They 2. ______ to capture realism, using techniques like chiaroscuro to create depth and shadow. This period saw a shift 3. ______ religious themes to a celebration of individualism and classical knowledge. Artists like Leonardo da Vinci and Michelangelo left an incredible mark, 4. ________ art 5. ______ centuries.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Focused at&amp;quot; is less common in this context and usually implies directing something towards a specific point or target, rather than concentrating attention.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Focused in&amp;quot; is generally incorrect in this construction; &amp;quot;in&amp;quot; might refer to being inside something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;Focused with&amp;quot; would imply using something to focus, which doesn&amp;#39;t fit the meaning here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;aimed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence describes a general action or goal of artists during the Renaissance. The simple past tense &amp;quot;aimed&amp;quot; is appropriate for a completed action in that historical period.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Aimed to capture realism&amp;quot; indicates their consistent objective throughout that era.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Complete Passage: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;During the Renaissance, artists focused (1) &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;on&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/u&gt;depicting the beauty of the human form and nature. They 2. &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;aimed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; to capture realism, using techniques like chiaroscuro to create depth and shadow. This period saw a shift (3) ______ religious themes to a celebration of individualism and classical knowledge. Artists like Leonardo da Vinci and Michelangelo left an incredible mark, (4)________ art (5)______ centuries.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
