	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;also&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; functions as an adverb, not a conjunction between two adjectives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;like&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence is: &amp;ldquo;Separating recyclables (2) _____ paper, plastic and glass from regular waste reduces landfill waste.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct preposition to show examples or categories is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;like&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;Like&amp;rsquo; is used to give examples &amp;mdash; for instance, &amp;ldquo;items like bottles and cans.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct phrase is &amp;ldquo;recyclables &lt;strong&gt;like paper, plastic and glass&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Such:&lt;/strong&gt; Used for emphasis or to indicate a degree, not suitable before examples.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Similar to:&lt;/strong&gt; Used for comparison, not listing examples.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dislike:&lt;/strong&gt; A verb meaning &amp;#39;not to like&amp;#39;, grammatically incorrect in this context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The blank begins a participial phrase that shows the means or method by which something happens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;By&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is used to indicate the method or means (e.g., &lt;em&gt;By studying, she improved&lt;/em&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;By adopting this habit&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; correctly shows how individuals come to participate in sustainable practices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options (Again, Also, And) do not express the method/means and therefore are ungrammatical here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 &amp;mdash; Again:&lt;/strong&gt; (Incorrect) Means &amp;quot;once more&amp;quot; &amp;mdash; not suitable to introduce a means.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2 &amp;mdash; Also:&lt;/strong&gt; (Incorrect) Adds information but does not indicate method.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3 &amp;mdash; And:&lt;/strong&gt; (Incorrect) Joins clauses/words; does not express method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;actively&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage emphasizes individual involvement in sustainable practices through recycling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The verb phrase &amp;ldquo;participate in sustainable practices&amp;rdquo; requires an adverb that describes the manner of participation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;Actively&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; fits best because it means taking part with energy and commitment, aligning with the idea of responsible and engaged participation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options like &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;strong&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;vociferously&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;vehemently&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt; do not suit the tone or grammatical structure of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong:&lt;/strong&gt; An adjective, not suitable here since the blank requires an adverb.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vociferously:&lt;/strong&gt; Means loudly or forcefully &amp;mdash; does not fit the calm, positive tone of the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vehemently:&lt;/strong&gt; Implies intense emotion or anger &amp;mdash; contextually inappropriate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;responsible&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage emphasizes the importance of recycling and sustainable behavior at home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The blank refers to teaching future generations about a way of living that involves care and accountability toward the environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; fits the context as it describes living with awareness and accountability for one&amp;rsquo;s impact on nature.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options like &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;wisely&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;independent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; do not convey the ethical and environmental sense required here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wisely&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; means showing good judgment, but doesn&amp;rsquo;t emphasize moral responsibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Obligated&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; means being forced to do something; doesn&amp;rsquo;t fit naturally with &amp;ldquo;living.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independent&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; means self-reliant; unrelated to environmental awareness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1&lt;/b&gt; i.e., &lt;strong&gt;lad&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;lad&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a young boy or a teenaged male. (लड़का)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;lad &lt;/strong&gt;was excited to join his friends for a game of soccer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Teenaged boy&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a male who is in his teenage years, typically between 13 and 19 years old. (किशोर लड़का)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;teenaged boy &lt;/strong&gt;was keen to learn how to drive.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that a teenaged boy is informally called a &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lad&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt; i.e., &lt;strong&gt;lad&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lord&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;प्रभु&lt;/span&gt;): A title for a nobleman or someone with power and authority.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;lord &lt;/strong&gt;of the manor was respected by all the villagers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bachelor&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;कुंवारा&lt;/span&gt;): A man who is not and has never been married.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He lived a carefree life as a &lt;strong&gt;bachelor&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Youth&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;युवा&lt;/span&gt;): The period between childhood and adult age; a young person.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;youth &lt;/strong&gt;of today are more tech-savvy than ever before.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;the&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The article &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;the&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is used to specify a particular item that is known to both the speaker and the listener.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In this context, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the most expensive one&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; specifies a particular car that is the most expensive in the neighbourhood.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;an&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; do not fit the context as appropriately. &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;No word required&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is also not suitable as the sentence requires a definite article.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Vinod&amp;#39;s car is &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; most expensive one in our neighbourhood.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A (एक)&lt;/strong&gt;: is an indefinite article used before words that begin with a consonant sound.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An (एक)&lt;/strong&gt;: is an indefinite article used before words that begin with a vowel sound.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No word required&lt;/strong&gt;: suggests that the sentence does not need an article, which is incorrect in this context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Option &amp;#39;4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;Arraing&amp;nbsp;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The given sentence is asking for the INCORRECTLY spelt word among the options provided. The correct spelling of &amp;quot;Arraing&amp;quot; is &amp;quot;Arraign&amp;quot;. The options &amp;quot;Campaign&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Biennial&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;Cavalry&amp;quot; are spelt correctly. The structure of the question requires us to identify the misspelt word. Correct sentence:&amp;nbsp;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;4&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;Arraing&amp;nbsp;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Correct Spelling Examples: Campaign: A series of actions intended to accomplish a goal. Biennial: Happening every two years. Cavalry: Soldiers who fought on horseback. Incorrect Spelling Example: Arraign: To call or bring someone before a court to answer a criminal charge.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains Hume&amp;#39;s view that the shift from traditional, land-based wealth and responsibility to debt financing (stocks and bonds) changed the structure and culture of European society.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hume warned that debt financing was &amp;ldquo;destroying every part of society&amp;rdquo; and creating new sources of wealth and social mobility, different from the old landholding traditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Hume supported the British system of war financing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, Hume actually warned about its dangers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Land inheritance was always a source of instability in Britain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage states land inheritance provided stability and continuity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: The French Revolution was directly caused by debt financing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage does not make this claim.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the main idea of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hume argued that the rise of debt financing and financial instruments like stocks and bonds fundamentally transformed European society and its traditional structures&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage examines David Hume&amp;rsquo;s arguments about the impact of debt financing on European society in a logical, reasoned, and thoughtful manner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It analyzes the differences between traditional land-based wealth and the rise of financial instruments, and reflects on how these changes influenced social structure and culture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;There is no sarcasm, humor, or detachment; the style is analytical and reflective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Sarcastic and mocking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage is serious and reasoned.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Light-hearted and humorous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage treats the topic with seriousness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Indifferent and detached&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the author is engaged with the topic and provides thoughtful analysis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the tone of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;analytical and reflective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In his essay &amp;#39;Of Public Credit&amp;#39;, Hume warned about the dangers of Britain&amp;rsquo;s increasing reliance on debt financing and how this could transform society.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;He argued that debt financing&amp;mdash;through stocks and bonds&amp;mdash;could disrupt traditional structures and social responsibilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: The benefits of government saving money for future wars&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect. While Hume mentions historical practices, his main focus is warning about debt financing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: The importance of land inheritance in maintaining social stability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect. The passage discusses land inheritance as context, but Hume&amp;rsquo;s warning is about debt financing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: The need for more merchants to become landowners&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect. Hume notes this trend but does not argue for it as a solution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, Hume warned about &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the dangers of Britain&amp;rsquo;s increasing reliance on debt financing and its societal consequences&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains that debt financing (stocks and bonds) allowed wealth and power to move outside the traditional land-based system, enabling new social mobility and economic arrangements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This disrupted the established order, where land inheritance determined wealth, status, and responsibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Most people in Hume&amp;rsquo;s time changed professions frequently&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage states most people followed their parents&amp;#39; profession.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Debt financing had no influence on British society&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage argues the opposite.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Hume believed that financial innovation always led to more responsible citizens&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, Hume warned that financial innovation could undermine traditional responsibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, it can be concluded that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;debt financing created new forms of social mobility and economic power, disrupting traditional society based on land and inheritance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option (2) i.e. Catastrophic&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;apocalyptic&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means describing or predicting a catastrophic or disastrous event, often involving the end of the world or widespread destruction. (विनाशकारी / प्रलयकारी)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The movie showed an apocalyptic vision of the future where cities were destroyed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Catastrophic&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is a synonym of &amp;ldquo;apocalyptic&amp;rdquo;, as both refer to events causing great and sudden damage or suffering. (विनाशकारी)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The earthquake had catastrophic consequences for the region.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the most appropriate synonym of &amp;ldquo;apocalyptic&amp;rdquo; is &amp;ldquo;catastrophic&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is- Catastrophic&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimistic&lt;/strong&gt; (आशावादी): Hopeful and confident about the future.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She is optimistic about her chances of winning the competition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Boring&lt;/strong&gt; (उबाऊ): Not interesting; dull.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The lecture was so boring that many students fell asleep.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traditional&lt;/strong&gt; (परंपरागत): Existing in or as part of a tradition; long-established.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The festival is celebrated in the traditional way every year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage details how Bose&amp;rsquo;s insight&amp;mdash;treating light quanta as indistinguishable particles&amp;mdash;transformed quantum statistics and validated Einstein&amp;rsquo;s ideas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Bose&amp;rsquo;s approach led to a new derivation of Planck&amp;rsquo;s law and, via Einstein&amp;rsquo;s extension, to the prediction of the Bose-Einstein condensate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage also highlights the initial challenges Bose faced in gaining recognition, and the enthusiastic support he received from Einstein.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Einstein disagreed with Bose&amp;rsquo;s statistical methods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, Einstein praised and promoted Bose&amp;rsquo;s work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Light quanta were always accepted by European physicists&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage notes there was skepticism toward the photon concept.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Bose&amp;rsquo;s work was quickly recognized in Britain&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, his work was initially ignored by the British journal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the main idea of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Bose revolutionized the understanding of quantum statistics by treating light quanta as indistinguishable, leading to major advances in physics and the eventual discovery of the Bose-Einstein condensate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage examines Bose&amp;rsquo;s scientific contributions in a logical and systematic (analytical) manner, explaining how his insights advanced quantum physics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It also expresses admiration and respect (appreciative) for Bose&amp;rsquo;s achievements and for Einstein&amp;rsquo;s recognition and support of his work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Critical and dismissive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage praises Bose&amp;rsquo;s innovation and determination.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Humorous and satirical&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage maintains a serious and respectful tone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Indifferent and detached&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage is engaged and appreciative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the tone of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;analytical and appreciative&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Bose sent his manuscript directly to Einstein because his work was ignored by the British journal Philosophical Magazine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage states his submission was &amp;quot;met with silence&amp;quot; and suggests this could have been due to bias against colonial scientists or uncertainty about the work&amp;rsquo;s importance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Undeterred, Bose sought Einstein&amp;rsquo;s opinion and assistance in publishing his paper.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Because he wanted to criticize Einstein&amp;rsquo;s 1905 theory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, Bose admired and extended Einstein&amp;rsquo;s theory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Because he was seeking a job in Europe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, there is no mention of seeking employment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Because Einstein had previously published similar work&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;While Einstein&amp;rsquo;s work was related, the reason Bose wrote to him was the lack of response from the British journal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, Bose sent his manuscript directly to Einstein &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;because his work was ignored by the British journal Philosophical Magazine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage suggests that the British journal Philosophical Magazine&amp;rsquo;s silence toward Bose&amp;rsquo;s paper may have been an example of the biases that colonial scientists often faced.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This possible bias could have delayed the recognition and publication of Bose&amp;rsquo;s groundbreaking work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Einstein was the first to treat photons as indistinguishable particles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage credits Bose with this key insight.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: The Bose-Einstein condensate was predicted and immediately observed in the 1920s.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage states it was not detected experimentally until the 1990s.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Bose&amp;rsquo;s statistical approach was based on classical reasoning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage notes that previous approaches used classical reasoning, but Bose&amp;rsquo;s was novel and quantum-based.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, it can be concluded that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;biases against colonial scientists possibly delayed recognition of Bose&amp;rsquo;s work&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option (2) i.e. Bold&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;audacious&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means showing a willingness to take surprisingly bold risks; daring or fearless. (साहसी / निर्भीक)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The explorers made an audacious journey across the unknown desert.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Bold&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct meaning of &amp;ldquo;audacious&amp;rdquo;. (साहसी)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Her bold decision to start her own business was truly audacious.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, &amp;ldquo;audacious&amp;rdquo; as used in the passage means &amp;ldquo;bold&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is- Bold&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cowardly&lt;/strong&gt; (कायर): Lacking courage; easily frightened.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The soldier&amp;rsquo;s cowardly behaviour disappointed his comrades.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unintentional&lt;/strong&gt; (अनजाने में): Not done on purpose.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The mistake was unintentional and quickly corrected.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unscientific&lt;/strong&gt; (अवैज्ञानिक): Not based on or conforming to the principles of science.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His unscientific approach led to unreliable results.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage critiques the medical profession&amp;rsquo;s culture of authority and confidence, showing how overconfidence can lead to errors and is sometimes reinforced by patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It calls for examining medicine from multiple perspectives&amp;mdash;philosophy, sociology, psychology, and patient experiences&amp;mdash;to challenge myths and improve the field.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Only doctors can accurately diagnose and treat patients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage argues against the myth of the irreplaceable doctor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: All professions are immune to criticism and change&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage gives examples of professions that have changed over time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Philosophers are better decision-makers than clinicians&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage notes that clinicians must make quick, high-stakes decisions unlike philosophers, but does not claim philosophers are better.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the main idea of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the culture of medicine often overvalues confidence and authority, leading to overconfidence and errors, and needs to be examined from multiple perspectives, including those of outsiders and patients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage critically examines the overconfidence and authority within the medical profession and reflects on how this culture is reinforced by both doctors and patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It also reflects on the need to question long-held myths and to consider insights from multiple perspectives for meaningful improvement in medicine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Light-hearted and humorous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, as the passage addresses serious flaws in medical culture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Indifferent and passive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the tone is engaged and evaluative, not indifferent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Optimistic and celebratory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage is critical and calls for change, not celebration.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the tone of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;critical and reflective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Patients tend to prefer confident doctors because the white coat as a symbol of authority and doctors&amp;rsquo; decisiveness provide reassurance, even if the confidence is misplaced.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explicitly states that patients are reassured by confidence and decisiveness, even when it does not correlate with accuracy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Because confidence always ensures accuracy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage shows that confidence is not a guarantee of accuracy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Because doctors always seek second opinions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage states that experienced doctors tend to seek fewer second opinions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Because confidence has no impact on medical outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage addresses how misplaced confidence can lead to errors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, patients prefer confident doctors &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;because the symbol of the white coat and decisiveness reassure patients, even if the confidence is misplaced&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains that overconfidence in medicine is not only a problem among doctors (who may consult less as they gain experience) but is also reinforced by patients, who prefer confident doctors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It also discusses the persistent myth of the irreplaceable doctor, which hinders reform and adaptation in the medical field.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: Doctors are never wrong when they act decisively.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage specifically notes that confidence does not ensure accuracy and that doctors can be wrong even when certain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Patients usually distrust confident doctors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage says patients are reassured by confidence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Medicine has always openly acknowledged its diagnostic errors.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage notes that diagnostic error was largely ignored for most of medical history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, it can be concluded that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;overconfidence in medicine is reinforced by both doctors and patients, and the myth of the irreplaceable doctor hinders necessary changes in the field&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option (3) i.e. Substitute&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;proxy&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means a person or thing that acts or stands in for another; a substitute or representative. (प्रतिनिधि / विकल्प)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She attended the meeting as a proxy for her manager.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Substitute&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct meaning of &amp;ldquo;proxy&amp;rdquo; as used in the passage. (विकल्प)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; In some online systems, you can use a proxy server as a substitute for your real server.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &amp;ldquo;proxy&amp;rdquo; means &amp;ldquo;substitute&amp;rdquo; in the given context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is- Substitute&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tradition&lt;/strong&gt; (परंपरा): A custom or belief passed down through generations.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Lighting lamps is a tradition during Diwali.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guarantee&lt;/strong&gt; (गारंटी): A formal promise or assurance.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The product comes with a two-year guarantee.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Obstacle&lt;/strong&gt; (बाधा): Something that blocks or hinders progress.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Fear of failure can be a major obstacle to success.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage traces the history of the idea that humans can learn while asleep, focusing on hypnopaedia and inventions like the Psycho-Phone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It describes the initial enthusiasm, commercialization, and seeming scientific support for sleep learning, followed by the eventual scientific debunking using EEG technology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: The Psycho-Phone was the most successful invention of the 20th century.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage does not claim this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Hypnopaedia has always been rejected by scientists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, it was once widely accepted and promoted before being disproved.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: All sleep-related inventions have been unsuccessful.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage only critiques sleep-learning, not all sleep inventions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the main idea of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the concept of learning during sleep, or hypnopaedia, has a long history and was once popularized and commercialized, but ultimately scientific evidence failed to support its effectiveness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage carefully examines the historical development, commercialization, and scientific evaluation of sleep learning (hypnopaedia).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It presents the facts and evidence in a logical, analytical manner, and maintains a mildly skeptical attitude toward the claims of hypnopaedia, especially as scientific testing disproved its effectiveness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: Jubilant and celebratory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage does not celebrate hypnopaedia; it critiques it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Indifferent and detached&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage is engaged and investigative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Aggressive and confrontational&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage critiques without aggression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the tone of the passage is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;analytical and mildly skeptical&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage states that the decline in hypnopaedia&amp;rsquo;s popularity came in the 1950s, when scientists began using EEG to confirm that participants were truly asleep during experiments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;EEG studies showed that learning while genuinely asleep was ineffective, leading to the technique&amp;rsquo;s decline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 1: People became less interested in learning foreign languages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the decline was due to scientific findings, not lack of interest.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: The Soviet Union banned the technique.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage does not mention a ban.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: The Psycho-Phone became too expensive.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, cost is not discussed as a reason for the decline.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, the popularity of hypnopaedia declined in the 1950s because &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;EEG studies showed that learning while truly asleep was ineffective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains that early studies on hypnopaedia lacked reliable methods to distinguish between subjects who were truly asleep and those who were just resting or drowsy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Only with the use of EEG in the 1950s could scientists confirm the subjects&amp;rsquo; true sleep state, revealing that actual sleep learning was ineffective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 2: The Psycho-Phone was proven to significantly improve confidence in all users.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, there is no scientific evidence supporting this claim in the passage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 3: Aldous Huxley invented the concept of sleep learning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage notes the idea predates Huxley, though he popularized it in fiction.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option 4: Learning during sleep is now widely accepted by scientists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Incorrect, the passage states that scientific evidence did not support sleep learning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;Therefore, it can be concluded that &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;early studies supporting hypnopaedia did not reliably distinguish between actual sleep and mere rest or drowsiness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option (2) i.e. Negative reaction&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;backlash&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means a strong and adverse reaction to an idea, action, or event, often from the public or a group. (प्रतिक्रिया / प्रतिरोध)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The new policy caused a public backlash, with many people protesting against it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Negative reaction&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct meaning of &amp;ldquo;backlash&amp;rdquo; as used in the passage. (नकारात्मक प्रतिक्रिया)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; There was a significant backlash from the employees after the changes were announced.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &amp;ldquo;backlash&amp;rdquo; means &amp;ldquo;negative reaction&amp;rdquo; in the given context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is- Negative reaction&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sudden support&lt;/strong&gt; (अचानक समर्थन): Quick and unexpected help.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The leader received sudden support from the youth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scientific innovation&lt;/strong&gt; (वैज्ञानिक नवाचार): A new discovery or invention in science.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The vaccine is a major scientific innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sleep disorder&lt;/strong&gt; (नींद से संबंधित समस्या): A medical condition that affects a person&amp;#39;s ability to sleep well.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Insomnia is a common sleep disorder.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
